'''波兰境内的犹太人大屠杀'''是[[纳粹德国|纳粹德国]]在[[波兰第二共和国|波兰占领区]]内实施的[[种族灭绝|种族灭绝]]行动，以专门建造的[[滅絕營|滅絕營]]为特征。[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]期间，第三帝国的[[猶太人大屠殺|猶太人大屠殺]]夺走了300万[[波兰犹太人历史|波兰犹太人]]的生命，{{r|IPN2009}}占大屠杀中全部犹太人遇难者的半数。在德国的灭绝行动中，另有多达300万的[[波蘭人|波兰裔]]受害者，但学者们对于是否将他们同样归于犹太人大屠杀受害者仍有争议。<ref name="ColumbiaGuide"/>
纳粹[[最终解决方案|系统性杀害]]了超过90%的[[波兰第二共和国|波兰]][[波兰犹太人历史|犹太人人口]]，德国建立的灭绝营在其中起到了核心作用。{{r|Berenbaum104}}

德国繁复的官僚机构的每个部门都参与了杀戮过程，从内政部、财政部到德国企业与[[大屠殺列車|国营铁路]]。{{r|trains}}{{r|Gigliotti55}}德国公司竞标合同，在[[波蘭總督府|波蘭總督府]]和其他地区的集中营中建造焚尸炉。{{r|Berenbaum104|AJC}}

在德国占领期间，即使会让自己和家人付出最为高昂的代价，仍有许多[[波蘭人|波蘭人]]成功地从德国人手中救下了犹太人。 在大屠杀期间救援犹太人的各国援救者中，波兰籍援救者的人数是最多的。{{r|Lukas1989}}{{r|YV Stats}}[[以色列|以色列]]已认定了{{Polish Righteous count}}名{{tsl|en|Polish Righteous among the Nations|波兰国际义人}}。<ref>{{Harvp|www.yadvashem.org|2019}}</ref>

只有一小部分[[波兰犹太人历史|波兰犹太人]]在[[德苏占领波兰|德占波兰]]境内幸存下来。有一些向东逃出德国人的占领范围，进入1939年时[[苏联吞并的波兰领土|被苏联吞并的波兰领土]]，<ref>{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|loc=Preface.}}</ref>却和多达100万人的波兰非犹太公民一同被发配到[[西伯利亚|西伯利亚]]强制劳役。{{r|Levin347}}<ref name=Szarota2009>{{harvp|Materski|Szarota|2009|loc=''Source:'' Z.S. Siemaszko (1991), p. 95. {{ISBN|0850652103}}.}}</ref>

==背景==
{{main|德苏占领波兰|纳粹对波兰民族的罪行|{{tsl|en|War crimes in occupied Poland during World War II|第二次世界大战时期波兰境内发生的战争罪行}}}}

在波兰沦陷前，波兰第二共和国政府就曾经对境内的犹太人进行屠杀和驱逐，而到了1939年[[波蘭戰役|入侵波兰]]之后，根据《[[苏德互不侵犯条约|莫洛托夫-里宾特洛甫条约]]》的秘密议定书，{{r|Sellars2013}}纳粹德国和苏联将波兰划分为[[德苏占领波兰|各自的占领区]]。波兰[[纳粹德国吞并的波兰领土|西部的大片地区]]被德国吞并。{{r|Eber25-29}}苏联试图欺骗波兰人，使波兰人相信红军进入波兰东部是为了共同打击德国；{{r|DGW127}}随后占领了[[波兰第二共和国|战前波兰]]约52％的领土。在恐惧的气氛下，[[内务人民委员部|内务人民委员部]]和红军安排了一场{{tsl|en|Elections to the People's Assemblies of Western Ukraine and Western Belarus|西乌克兰与西白俄罗斯人民代表大会选举|做样子的公投}}(有争议)，{{r|Wegner-74}}{{r|RMoor28}}苏联随即吞并了整个[[波兰前东部领土|波兰前东部领土]]地区。苏联吞并的地区居住着1320至1370万人，{{r|Eber25-29}}{{r|Tr-Maz}}包括大量的乌克兰族和白俄罗斯族，以及130万犹太人。几个月之内，[[波兰犹太人历史|东部波兰犹太人]]与幸存的波兰人一起被安置到苏联内地深处。约有20-23万名波兰犹太人男性、女性和儿童被苏联安排离境。{{r|Buwalda}}{{r|Joc/Lew2010}}

随着1941年6月22日[[德意志國防軍|德国军队]]入侵[[德苏占领波兰|苏联占领区]]，两国早些时候在莫斯科签署的[[苏德互不侵犯条约|互不侵犯条约]]被撕毁。1941年到1943年间，波兰全境处于德国的控制之下。<ref>{{harvp|Eberhardt|Owsinski|2003|pp=199-201}}</ref> 纳粹在波兰中部和东南部建立了半殖民地性质的[[波蘭總督府|波蘭總督府]]，面积占原波兰领土的39％.{{r|distrikt}}

==纳粹的隔都化政策==
{{further|德占波兰的犹太人隔都|{{tsl|en|Intelligenzaktion|知识分子行动}}}}

在第二次世界大战之前，波兰有350万犹太人，<ref name="Schudrich">{{harvp|Cherry|Orla-Bukowska|2007|p=137|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=gUp7AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA137&dq=%223%2C500%2C000+Jews%22+%22in+Poland%22  'Part III Introduction' by Michael Schudrich.]}}</ref>主要居住在城市中；犹太人口约占波兰总人口的10％. [[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|波蘭猶太人歷史博物館]]的数据库提供了全国1,926个犹太社区的信息。{{r|statistics}}德国在征服波兰和1939年{{tsl|en|Intelligenzaktion|知识分子行动|屠杀知识分子}}之后，<ref>{{citation |first=Maria |last=Wardzyńska |title=The Year was 1939: Operation of German Security Police in Poland. Intelligenzaktion |work=(Był rok 1939. Operacja niemieckiej policji bezpieczeństwa w Polsce. Intelligenzaktion) |year=2009 |url=http://pamiec.pl/download/49/34737/BYLROK1939.pdf |publisher=[[国家记忆研究院|Institute of National Remembrance]] |isbn=978-83-7629-063-8 |id=PDF file, direct download 2.56 MB |language=pl |at=pp. 8–10 in current document |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129035451/http://pamiec.pl/download/49/34737/BYLROK1939.pdf |archivedate=2014-11-29 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}.</ref>德国的第一项反犹太措施涉及将犹太人驱逐出[[纳粹德国吞并的波兰领土|第三帝国吞并领土]]的政策。<ref>{{citation |title=The Holocaust: the Jewish tragedy |first=Martin |last=Gilbert |publisher=Collins |year=1986 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hRJnAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22the%20trapping%20of%20Polish%20Jewry%22 |pages=84–85 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819115646/https://books.google.com/books?id=hRJnAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22the%20trapping%20of%20Polish%20Jewry%22 |dead-url=no }}.</ref>位于最西部的省份[[大波兰|大波兰]]和[[東波美拉尼亞|東波美拉尼亞]]变成了全新的德国[[帝國大區|帝國大區]]，即[[但泽－西普鲁士帝国大区|但泽－西普鲁士帝国大区]]与[[瓦尔特兰帝国大区|瓦尔特兰帝国大区]]，<ref name="Łuczak">{{cite book |author={{tsl|en|Czesław Łuczak||Czesław Łuczak}} |title=Położenie ludności polskiej w Kraju Warty 1939–1945. Dokumenty niemieckie |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gksNAAAAIAAJ|publisher=Wydawn. Poznańskie |location=[[波茲南|Poznań]] |year=1987 |pages=V–XIII |id=Google Books |isbn=978-83-210-0632-1}}</ref>旨在是通过移居者殖民（“[[生存空间|生存空间]]”）实现完全[[德國化|德國化]]。<ref>{{cite web |year=2013 |title=Poles: Victims of the Nazi Era |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |url=http://www.ushmm.org/learn/students/learning-materials-and-resources/poles-victims-of-the-nazi-era |id=[https://web.archive.org/web/20140117131606/http://www.ushmm.org/m/pdfs/2000926-Poles.pdf (PDF version)] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003002131/http://www.ushmm.org/learn/students/learning-materials-and-resources/poles-victims-of-the-nazi-era|archivedate=October 3, 2013 }}</ref>罗兹市直接附属于新的Warthegau地区，吸收了大约4万名自周围地区驱逐出来的波兰犹太人。<ref name="jewishgen/timeline">{{cite web |url=http://kehilalinks.jewishgen.org/lodz/statistics.htm |title=Lodz Ghetto Deportations and Statistics |publisher=JewishGen Home Page |work=Timeline |date=2007 |accessdate=26 March 2015 |first=Shirley |last=Rotbein Flaum |quote=''Source:'' Encyclopedia of the Holocaust (1990), Baranowski, Dobroszycki, Wiesenthal, Yad Vashem Timeline of the Holocaust, others. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321021602/http://kehilalinks.jewishgen.org/lodz/statistics.htm |archivedate=2015-03-21 }}</ref>共有20.4万名犹太人经过[[羅茲猶太區|罗兹隔都]]。依照最初的计划，他们将被驱逐到[[波蘭總督府|波兰总督府]]；<ref>{{cite web |first=Jennifer |last=Rosenberg |year=2006 |title=The Łódź Ghetto |quote=Sources: ''Lodz Ghetto: Inside a Community Under Siege'' by Adelson, Alan and Robert Lapides (ed.), New York, 1989; ''The Documents of the Łódź Ghetto: An Inventory of the Nachman Zonabend Collection'' by Web, Marek (ed.), New York, 1988; ''The Holocaust: The Fate of European Jewry'' by Yahil, Leni, New York, 1991. |url=http://history1900s.about.com/library/holocaust/aa070897.htm |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060430213432/http://history1900s.about.com/library/holocaust/aa070897.htm |archivedate=2006-04-30 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}</ref><ref name="JVL">{{cite web |url=http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/lodz.html |title=The Lódz Ghetto (1939–1945) |publisher=Jewish Virtual Library|work=History & Overview |orig-year=1998 |year=2015 |accessdate=19 March 2015 |first=Jennifer |last=Rosenberg |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402120747/https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/lodz.html |archivedate=April 2, 2015 }}</ref>然而大规模移除犹太人的最终目的地迟迟不决，直到两年后[[最终解决方案|最终解决方案]]启动为止。<ref>{{cite book|first1=Moishe |last1=Postone |first2=Eric L. |last2=Santner |year=2003 |title=Catastrophe and Meaning: The Holocaust and the Twentieth Century |publisher=University of Chicago Press |isbn=978-0-226-67610-4 |pp=75–6 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zGKOH1XxK8UC&q=measures+ghettoization |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=zGKOH1XxK8UC&q=measures+ghettoization |archivedate=July 5, 2018 }}</ref>

[[File:The_Mass_Extermination_of_Jews_in_German_Occupied.pdf|thumb]]向[[同盟國_(第二次世界大戰)|战时]][[聯合國共同宣言|联合国]]递交的出版物]]

德国占领当局在入侵后立即开始迫害波兰犹太人，特别是在主要城市地区。在头一年半的时间里，纳粹仅仅是剥夺犹太人的贵重物品和财产以获取利润，{{r|Berenbaum104}}将他们[[德占波兰的犹太人隔都|赶入临时的隔都]]，并迫使他们为公共工程和战争经济从事{{tsl|en|Forced labour under German rule during World War II|第二次世界大战期间德国统治下的强制劳动|奴隶劳动}}。<ref>{{citation |title=Jewish Forced Labor Under the Nazis: Economic Needs and Racial Aims, 1938–1944 |first=Wolf |last=Gruner |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2006 |quote=By the end of 1940, the forced-labor program in the [[波蘭總督府|General Government]] had registered over 700,000 Jewish men and women who were working for the German economy in ghetto businesses and as labor for projects outside the ghetto; there would be more. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DJqIqwj_P70C&q=1940+forced-labor+700%2C000 |pages=249–250 |isbn=978-0521838757 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200511000712/https://books.google.com/books?id=DJqIqwj_P70C&q=1940+forced-labor+700,000 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在此期间，德国人命令犹太社区任命[[犹太人委员会|犹太人委员会]]管理隔都，从而“以最严格的方式”负责执行命令。<ref name="Trunk1972">{{cite book |first=Isaiah |last=Trunk |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D7bobfzrcCoC |title=Judenrat: the Jewish Councils in Eastern Europe under Nazi Occupation |id=with an introduction by Jacob Robinson |location=New York |publisher=Macmillan |year=1972 |isbn=978-0-8032-9428-8 |pages=5, 172, 352 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930113008/https://books.google.com/books?id=D7bobfzrcCoC |dead-url=no }}</ref>大多数隔都都建立在犹太人生活井井有条的城镇。出于后勤原因，没有铁路连接的德占区定居点中的犹太人社区被解散。<ref name="holocaustchronicle">{{cite web |url=http://www.holocaustchronicle.org/staticpages/176.html |title=1939: The War Against the Jews |author=Louis Weber, Contributing Writers |publisher=Publications International |date=April 2000 |work=The Holocaust Chronicle: A History in Words and Pictures|via=Internet Archive  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320005350/http://www.holocaustchronicle.org/staticpages/176.html|archivedate=March 20, 2012 }}</ref>在一项涉及使用[[大屠殺列車|货运列车]]的大规模驱逐行动中，全体波兰犹太人被集中在与现有铁路走廊相邻的{{tsl|en|Nazi ghettos|纳粹隔都|破败街区}}（Jüdischer Wohnbezirk），与其他社区隔离开来。<ref name="Berenbaum">{{cite book |author={{tsl|en|Michael Berenbaum||Michael Berenbaum}} |title=The World Must Know |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iqMWAQAAIAAJ |publisher=[[美国大屠杀纪念博物馆|United States Holocaust Memorial Museum]] |year=2006 |page=114 |isbn=9780801883583 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212011751/https://books.google.com/books?id=iqMWAQAAIAAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>粮食供给完全取决于[[党卫队|党卫队]]。<ref name="holocaust-education.dk">{{citation |authors=Peter Vogelsang, Brian Larsen |url=http://www.holocaust-education.dk/holocaust/ghettoer.asp |title=The Ghettos of Poland |publisher=''The Danish Center for Holocaust and Genocide Studies'' |year=2002 |via=Internet Archive |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306055255/http://www.holocaust-education.dk/holocaust/ghettoer.asp |archivedate=March 6, 2016 }}</ref>最初，犹太人被法律禁止烘焙面包; <ref name="Edelman-upenn">{{cite web |url=http://www.writing.upenn.edu/~afilreis/Holocaust/warsaw-uprising.html |title=The Ghetto Fights |publisher=Literature of the Holocaust, at the University of Pennsylvania |work=The Warsaw Ghetto: The 45th Anniversary of the Uprising |author=Marek Edelman |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091125114636/http://www.writing.upenn.edu/~afilreis/Holocaust/warsaw-uprising.html |archivedate=November 25, 2009 }}</ref>纳粹以不可持续的方式将犹太人与公众隔绝。{{r|holocaust-education.dk}}

{{quote|[[華沙猶太區|华沙隔都]]包含的犹太人比全法国都多；[[羅茲猶太區|罗兹隔都]]的犹太人比荷兰的所有犹太人都多。居住在[[克拉科夫猶太人區|克拉科夫市]]的犹太人人数超过了整个意大利，而几乎每个波兰中等城镇的犹太人口都超过了全斯堪的纳维亚半岛的数目。整个欧洲东南部——匈牙利、罗马尼亚、保加利亚、南斯拉夫和希腊——的犹太人人数比[[波蘭總督府|波蘭總督府]]最初的四个区还要少。<ref name="CRB/Path">{{cite book |last=Browning |first=Christopher |title=The Path to Genocide: Essays on Launching the Final Solution |year=1995 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d9Wg4gjtP3cC&q=Warsaw%2BCracow%2BItaly |via=Google Books |isbn=978-0-521-55878-5 |ref=harv |page=194 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2019-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929220805/https://books.google.com/books?id=d9Wg4gjtP3cC |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}

在饱受战争蹂躏的波兰，犹太人口的萎缩可以按照{{tsl|en|Ghettos in Nazi-occupied Europe|欧洲纳粹占领区的隔都|隔都的存在}}划分为不同阶段。在隔都成立之前，<ref name="Gutman12">{{cite book |last=Gutman |first=Yisrael |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4U_OcvXvhF4C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=%22Warsaw%27s%20conditions%20of%20surrender%22&f=false |title=The First Months of the Nazi Occupation |publisher=Indiana University Press |work=The Jews of Warsaw, 1939–1943: Ghetto, Underground, Revolt |date=1989 |page=12 |isbn=978-0-253-20511-7 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200511000655/https://books.google.com/books?id=4U_OcvXvhF4C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=%22Warsaw%27s%20conditions%20of%20surrender%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>犹太人逃避迫害不会涉及法外的死刑处罚。{{r|ringelblum}}一旦隔都与外界隔绝，饥饿和疾病导致的死亡变得猖獗。走私食品和药品是唯一的缓解方法，{{tsl|en|Emanuel Ringelblum|伊曼纽尔·林格布鲁姆|林格布鲁姆}}称之为“两个民族间历史上最精彩的一页”。{{r|ringelblum}}在华沙，[[華沙猶太區|隔都]]消耗的食物中有高达80％是非法带入的。德国人推出的食品券提供了生存所需卡路里的9％.<ref name=Laqueur>{{citation |title=The Holocaust Encyclopedia |authors=Walter Laqueur, Judith Tydor Baumel |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2001 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nPbr0XzlTzcC&q=Warsaw+caloric+rations |pages=260–262|isbn=978-0300138115}}</ref>在1940年11月至1943年5月的两年半时间里，约有10万犹太人在华沙隔都死于饥饿和疾病；1940年5月至1944年8月之间的四年多时间里，罗兹隔都大约有4万人死于类似原因。{{r|Laqueur}}到1941年底，隔都的大多数犹太人没有任何储蓄来支付党卫队进一步提供的散装食物的费用。{{r|Laqueur}}德国当局中的“生产主义者”试图通过将隔都变成企业来使其自我维持，他们的意见仅在德国袭击[[波兰前东部领土|波兰东部]]的苏联占领区（即[[巴巴羅薩行動|巴巴羅薩行動]]）之后才压过“消耗主义者”。<ref name="Browning2005">{{citation |title=Before the "Final Solution": Nazi Ghettoization Policy in Poland (1940–1941) |first=Christopher |last=Browning |publisher=Center for Advanced Holocaust Studies. United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |year=2005|url=https://www.ushmm.org/m/pdfs/20050823-ghettos-symposium.pdf |at=pp. 13–17 of 175 in current document |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222011246/https://www.ushmm.org/m/pdfs/20050823-ghettos-symposium.pdf |archivedate=December 22, 2016 }}.</ref>最主要的隔都通过生产[[苏德战争|东部前线]]所需的货物得到稳定{{r|holocaust-education.dk}}，犹太人口的死亡率开始下降（至少是暂时的）。{{r|Browning2005}}

==大规模枪决==
{{further|别动队|{{tsl|en|Schutzmannschaft|辅助警察(纳粹德国)|辅助警察}}|{{tsl|en|Collaboration with the Axis Powers during World War II|第二次世界大战时期的轴心国协作主义}}}}
[[File:Nazi_Holocaust_by_bullets_-_Jewish_mass_grave_near_Zolochiv,_west_Ukraine.jpg|thumb]]的犹太人被枪决后面朝下倒在[[佐洛乔夫|佐洛乔夫]]附近的一个露天大坑里。]]

随着1941年6月德国袭击苏联，[[海因里希·希姆莱|希姆莱]]召集了一支约11,000人的部队，首次实施了一项消灭犹太人的计划。<ref>{{harvp|Browning|2004|p= 229|ps=.}}</ref>巴巴罗萨行动期间，党卫隊还从苏联国民中招募了{{tsl|en|collaborationist auxiliary police|协作者辅助警察}}。{{r|USHMM1|Piotrowski1998_217}}当地的{{tsl|en|Schutzmannschaft|辅助警察(纳粹德国)|辅警}}为德国提供了人力，以及有关本地语言和地方的关键知识。<ref>{{cite book |title=Auxiliary Police Units in the Occupied Soviet Union, 1941–43 |first=Meredith M. |last=Meehan |publisher=USNA |year=2010|url=https://www.usna.edu/History/_files/documents/Honors-Program/2010/Meehan_Honors_Thesis.pdf |page=1 |quote=Without the auxiliaries, the Nazis' murderous intentions toward the Jewish population on the Eastern Front would not have been nearly as deadly. |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606073313/http://www.usna.edu/History/_files/documents/Honors-Program/2010/Meehan_Honors_Thesis.pdf |archivedate=June 6, 2016 }}</ref>在后来所谓的“子弹大屠杀”中，在乌克兰和立陶宛的{{tsl|en|Auxiliary Police Battalions|辅助警察营|辅助人员}}的援助下，[[秩序警察|德国警察营]]（Orpo）、[[保安警察_(纳粹德国)|安全警察]]（SiPo）、[[武装党卫队|武装党卫队]]与特殊[[別動隊|別動隊]]在前线后方执行独立于军队的任务，系统地枪决数万男女老幼。<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.ushmm.org/information/exhibitions/online-exhibitions/special-focus/desbois |title=Holocaust by Bullets |author=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum|year=2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811060650/https://www.ushmm.org/information/exhibitions/online-exhibitions/special-focus/desbois|archivedate=August 11, 2017 }}</ref>

波兰东部地区（原苏占区）中有超过30个地点发生了屠杀事件，<ref>{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|p=209|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=hC0-dk7vpM8C&q=fifty-one%20pogroms  'Pogroms involving murder.']}}</ref>，包括[[布列斯特隔都|布列斯特]]、[[塔尔诺波尔隔都|塔尔诺波尔]]与[[比亚韦斯托克隔都|比亚韦斯托克隔都]]等地，以及战前的省会城市{{tsl|en|Łuck Ghetto|卢茨克隔都|卢茨克}}、[[1941年利沃夫反犹骚乱|利沃夫]]、[[斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫隔都|斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫]]及[[維爾諾省|维尔纽斯]]（参见[[波納里大屠殺|博纳利大屠杀]]）<ref name="Headland">Ronald Headland (1992), ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=Mue8a5Rwyi0C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=%22Luck%2C%20Sonderkommando%22&f=false Messages of Murder: A Study of the Reports of the Einsatzgruppen of the Security Police and the Security Service, 1941–1943.]'' Fairleigh Dickinson Univ. Press, pp. 125–126.{{ISBN|0-8386-3418-4}}.</ref>大规模杀戮行动的幸存者被关押在新的用于剥削的隔都，<ref name="distrikt">{{cite book|last=Paczkowski |first=Andrzej |translator-first=Jane |translator-last=Cave |title=The Spring Will Be Ours: Poland and the Poles from Occupation to Freedom |year=2003 |publisher=[[宾夕法尼亚州立大学|Penn State]] Press |isbn=978-0-271-02308-3 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WoKQWem2yl4C&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54 |pages=54, 55–58 |via=Google Books |quote=Further Reading: [http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005130 "Einsatzgruppen," at the Holocaust Encyclopedia.] |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=WoKQWem2yl4C&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54 |archivedate=July 5, 2018 }}</ref>并且在德国当局的心血来潮下因{{tsl|en|Hunger Plan|饥饿计划|人为饥荒}}而慢慢饿死。<ref name="Browning121">{{harvp|Browning|2004|pp=121–130|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=d9Wg4gjtP3cC&q=artificial+famine "Artificial famine."]}}</ref>出于卫生考虑，成千上万因饥饿和虐待而死的人的尸体被埋葬在乱葬坑中。<ref name="ITF">{{cite journal |title=Report: Mass graves and killing sites in the Eastern part of Europe |url=http://www.holocaustremembrance.com/sites/default/files/MMWG_Killing_Sites.pdf |publisher=''Task Force for International Cooperation on Holocaust Education and Research'' (ITF) |author=Tal Bruttmann, Mémorial de la Shoah |year=2010 |location=Grenoble |quote=Mass graves resulting from deaths in the ghettos and various places of detention due to mistreatment, starvation ... concern the fate of several hundred thousand Jews. In the Warsaw ghetto alone, more than 100,000 Jews died and were buried in various places. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811034810/http://www.holocaustremembrance.com/sites/default/files/MMWG_Killing_Sites.pdf |archivedate=2016-08-11 |access-date=2019-03-19 }}</ref>1941年11月起，毒气车投入使用。{{r|Rhodes255}}截至12月，波兰东半部和苏联最西部的共和国共有439,800名犹太人被杀害。东部反对“犹太人种族”的“毁灭性战争”政策已成为各阶层德国人的常识。{{r|LYah1991}}在两年的时间里，东部的枪杀受害者总数已增加到61.8万至80万犹太人。<ref>{{harvp|Browning|2004|p=244|ps=: ''For the global events at the end of 1941, see [[莫斯科戰役|Battle of Moscow]].''}}</ref>{{r|Thacker}}在{{tsl|en|Einsatzgruppen reports|别动队报告|纳粹行刑队向柏林的报告}}中，[[德苏友好合作和边界划定条约|苏德边境]]后方的所有地区已经实现了“{{tsl|en|Judenfrei|去犹太化}}”。{{r|YBau5}}

==最终解决方案与隔都清场==
{{further|最终解决方案|{{tsl|en|German camps in occupied Poland during World War II|第二次世界大战时期德国在波兰的集中营}}|{{tsl|en|Extermination through labour|劳役灭绝}}}}
[[File:The_Black_Book_of_Poland_(21–24).jpg|thumb]]于1942年在伦敦出版。]]

1942年1月20日，在柏林附近举行的的[[萬湖會議|萬湖會議]]期间，[[波兰总督府|波兰总督府]]国务秘书{{tsl|en|Josef Bühler|约瑟夫·布勒}}敦促[[萊因哈德·海德里希|萊因哈德·海德里希]]尽快开始实施计划中的“犹太人问题的[[最终解决方案|最终解决方案]]”。<ref>{{citation |title=Minutes of the Conference |place=discovered in {{tsl|en|Martin Luther (diplomat)||Martin Luther}}'s files after the war |url=http://www.oradour.info/appendix/wannsee1.htm |publisher=''Selected Documents.'' Vol. 11: The Wannsee Protocol. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803214838/http://www.oradour.info/appendix/wannsee1.htm |archivedate=2017-08-03 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}</ref>当时[[瓦尔特兰帝国大区|瓦尔特兰]]的[[海乌姆诺灭绝营|海乌姆诺灭绝营]]已经以“重新安置”作为幌子，在几周的时间里尝试了以排放废气实现工业化杀戮的实验。<ref>{{citation |title=Masters of Death: The SS-Einsatzgruppen and the Invention of the Holocaust |author=Richard Rhodes |page=233 |publisher=Knopf Doubleday |year=2007 |isbn=978-0307426802 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SAQ94hR-YxQC&q=December+1941+vans |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200511000716/https://books.google.com/books?id=SAQ94hR-YxQC&q=December+1941+vans |dead-url=no }}</ref>被选中的隔都囚犯无一例外地被告知他们要去劳改营，并被要求随身携带行李。<ref>{{citation |title=The Train Journey: Transit, Captivity, and Witnessing in the Holocaust |author=Simone Gigliotti |publisher=Berghahn Books |page=45 |year=2009 |isbn=978-1571812681|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rS8YwPZHNrEC&q=going+somewhere+better |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=rS8YwPZHNrEC&q=going+somewhere+better |archivedate=July 5, 2018 }}</ref>许多犹太人相信了纳粹“转移营地”的说辞，因为驱逐也是隔都化过程的一部分。{{r|Lukas1989}}另一方面，自1941年9月以来，{{tsl|en|Lublin Reservation|卢布林保留地|卢布林区内}}一直在讨论通过固定毒气室实现大规模屠杀的想法。毒气室是新起草的[[莱茵哈德行动|莱茵哈德行动]]的先决条件。莱茵哈德行动的领导人由{{tsl|en|Odilo Globocnik|奥迪洛·格洛波奇尼克}}担任：他曾下令在[[贝乌热茨灭绝营|贝乌热茨]]、[[索比布尔集中营|索比布尔]]与[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡]]建造灭绝营。<ref name=Cesarani2004>{{citation |work=Holocaust: From the persecution of the Jews to mass murder |editors=David Cesarani, Sarah Kavanaugh |title=The Origins of Operation Reinhard |author=Bogdan Musial |pages=196–197 |isbn=978-0415275118 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=va3CMvKMGj0C&q=technical+prerequisite |year=2004 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200511000648/https://books.google.com/books?id=va3CMvKMGj0C&q=technical+prerequisite |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[马伊达内克集中营|马伊达内克]]和[[奥斯威辛集中营|奥斯威辛]]，固定毒气室的建设工作分别于3月和5月开始，使用[[齊克隆B|齊克隆B]]的实验随即展开。{{r|Cesarani2004}}1942年至1944年间是大屠杀最极端的时期，来自波兰和欧洲其它地方的数百万犹太人在六座[[灭绝营|灭绝营]]中遇害。尽管这些集中营有时被错误地称作“[[“波兰集中营”争议|波兰死亡营]]”，但莱因哈德行动中的所有集中营从来没有波兰警卫。所有杀戮中心都是由纳粹分子在严格保密下设计和运营的，并得到了乌克兰[[特拉夫尼基人|特拉夫尼基人]]的帮助。{{r|Cherry2}}平民被禁止接近这些杀人设施；如果有平民在集中营铁路附近被发现，他们往往会被枪杀。<ref>{{tsl|en|Edward Kopówka||Kopówka}} & Rytel-Andrianik (2011), [https://web.archive.org/web/20161104145619/http://www.polacyizydzi.com/dam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdfp. 405.][https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20161104145619%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 ] {{Wayback|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20161104145619%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 |date=20190919015242 }}</ref>

[[File:Auschwitz_e_Birkenau_con_neve.JPG|thumb]]I号营入口，大门上的标语为“[[勞動帶來自由|勞動帶來自由]]”（Arbeit macht frei）下图：奥斯维辛真正的[[滅絕營|滅絕營]]，位于附近的II号营比克瑙]]

1942年初春，[[波蘭總督府|波蘭總督府]]开始对境内的所有隔都实施系统清场，此时犹太人唯一的生存机会是逃到“雅利安地带”。德国人为所谓的“[[大屠殺列車|安置列车]]”实施围捕；几乎同一时期，德国的各大工程企业（包括HAHB、<ref>{{cite book |title=The Business of Genocide: The SS, Slave Labor, and the Concentration Camps |author=Michael Thad Allen |publisher=Univ of North Carolina Press |year=2005 |page=139 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AOqta5ALLNMC&q=HAHB+Majdanek+Auschwitz |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926060614/https://books.google.com/books?id=AOqta5ALLNMC&q=HAHB+Majdanek+Auschwitz |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[埃尔福特|埃尔福特]]的{{tsl|en|Topf and Sons}}、以及C.H. Kori GmbH等）为党卫队建造了灭绝设施，其建立与围捕行动直接相关。{{r|jewishvirtuallibrary}}{{r|umn}}{{r|straightdope}}

在其他[[納粹集中營|納粹集中營]]中，来自欧洲各地的囚犯被剥削用于德国的战争投入；而德国[[滅絕營|滅絕營]]是秘密的[[莱茵哈德行动|莱茵哈德行动]]的一部分，专门用于迅速消灭波兰和外国犹太人，在偏远的地点选址建造。身在柏林的[[海因里希·希姆莱|海因里希·希姆莱]]掌控灭绝计划，但他将波兰地区的工作委托给了{{tsl|en|Lublin Reservation|卢布林保留区}}的党卫队与警察司令{{tsl|en|Odilo Globocnik|奥迪洛·格洛波奇尼克}}；灭绝营的德国监督对希姆莱负责。<ref name="Fischel">{{cite book |title=The Holocaust |author=Jack Fischel |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |year=1998 |isbn=978-0-313-29879-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HrW-b3Q-3ewC&q=Globocnik+1941+Himmler |page=129 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819115735/https://books.google.com/books?id=HrW-b3Q-3ewC&q=Globocnik+1941+Himmler |dead-url=no }}</ref>营地选址、设施建设和人员培训基于一项类似的“[[種族優生|種族優生]]”计划——[[T-4行动|T-4行动]]。该计划在德国开发，是一项通过非自愿安乐死实现大规模屠杀的行动。{{r|darkness}}{{r|psychology}}

===“重新安置”项目===
倘若没有[[德意志国铁路|德意志国铁路]]，纳粹德国不可能实现如此规模的[[最终解决方案|最终解决方案]]。<ref>{{citation |title=German railways admits complicity in Holocaust |authors=Kate Connolly, Susanne Kill |location=Berlin |date=January 23, 2008|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/jan/23/secondworldwar.germany |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903120826/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/jan/23/secondworldwar.germany |archivedate=September 3, 2017 |newspaper=The Guardian }}</ref>对波兰和外国犹太人的灭绝行动必须依赖铁路和僻静的杀戮中心。[[大屠殺列車|大屠杀列车]]加大了灭绝的规模，加快了灭绝所需的时间；此外，[[鐵路貨車|货运列车]]的封闭性也减少了护卫所需的部队人数。铁路运输使纳粹德国人能够建造和运营更大、更高效的灭绝营，同时向全世界世界——乃至纳粹的受害者——公开伪造一项“重新安置”计划。{{r|trains}}{{r|faqs}}在一次电话交谈中，[[海因里希·希姆莱|海因里希·希姆莱]]告知[[马丁·鲍曼|马丁·鲍曼]]波兰的犹太人已被消灭，鲍曼博尔曼在回答时尖叫道：“他们没有被消灭，只是疏散，疏散，疏散！”{{r|Enghelberg63}}

[[File:Krakow_Ghetto_06694.jpg|thumb]]遭遇清场。各家各户步行到{{tsl|en|Prokocim|普罗克希姆}}火车站等待“重新安置”。列车的目的地是[[奥斯威辛集中营|奥斯维辛]]。]]

莱因哈德行动期间，相当数量的被驱逐者因窒息和口渴在运送途中死亡，具体数量未知；运输途中没有提供食物或水。棚车（Güterwagen）只配有简单的茅厕。一个被栅栏封住的小窗户提供极少的通风，往往导致多人窒息而死。<ref name="jewishsf11">{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishsf.com/content/2-0-/module/displaystory/story_id/25615/edition_id/498/format/html/displaystory.html |title=Holocaust survivor gives teens the straight story |publisher=Jewish news weekly of Northern California |date=April 22, 2005 |accessdate=April 15, 2015 |author=Joshua Brandt |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051126224024/http://www.jewishsf.com/content/2-0-/module/displaystory/story_id/25615/edition_id/498/format/html/displaystory.html |archivedate=November 26, 2005}}</ref>一位[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡起义]]的幸存者证实了一辆这样的火车自[[比亞瓦-波德拉斯卡|比亞瓦-波德拉斯卡]]出发。当密封的门打开时，车上总计约6,000名犹太囚犯中有90％因窒息致死。他们的尸体被扔进称作“[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|传染病院]]”（Lazaret）的阴燃万人坑。<ref>{{harvp|Kopówka|Rytel-Andrianik|2011|loc=[https://web.archive.org/web/20161104145619/http://www.polacyizydzi.com/dam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf p. 95 (96 in current document). Testimony of Samuel Rajzman.]}}[https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20161104145619%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 {{Wayback|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20161104145619%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 |date=20190919015242 }}</ref>数百万人在德国交通运输部的指导下，以[[大屠殺列車|类似的列车]]运送到灭绝营，并由{{tsl|en|Dehomag|迪霍瑪|IBM的一家子公司}}跟踪，直到1944年12月奥斯威辛-比克瑙集中营综合体正式关闭为止。{{r|upenn}}{{r|USHMM8}}

死亡工厂只是众多大规模灭绝方式中的一种。纳粹在波兰东部设有僻静的杀戮地点：有5万名犹太人自[[布列斯特隔都|布热西奇]]、[[別廖扎|別廖扎]]、[[伊萬諾沃_(白俄羅斯)|亚努夫]]、[[科布林|科布林]]、{{tsl|pl|Horodec|霍洛德茨}}、[[安托帕利|安托帕利]]等{{tsl|en|Ghettos in Nazi-occupied Europe|欧洲纳粹占领区的隔都|隔都}}以及[[東方總督轄區|東方總督轄區]]西部边界上的其它地点运往[[布隆纳山|布隆纳山]]，并在该地的行刑坑中处决；爆炸物被用来加速行刑坑的挖掘过程。<ref name="sztetl.org">{{cite web |author=AŻIH |url=http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/bronna-gora/13,sites-of-martyrdom/23737,bronna-gora-bronnaja-gora-miejsce-masowych-egzekucji |title=Bronna Góra – Holocaust mass murder site |trans-title=Bronna Góra – miejsce masowych egzekucji |publisher=[[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|Museum of the History of Polish Jews]] ''[[Virtual_Shtetl|Virtual Shtetl]]'' |year=2014 |quote=Testimony of B. Wulf, Docket nr 301/2212, Archives of the {{tsl|en|Jewish Historical Institute||Jewish Historical Institute}} in Warsaw. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803212045/http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/bronna-gora/13,sites-of-martyrdom/23737,bronna-gora-bronnaja-gora-miejsce-masowych-egzekucji/ |archivedate=2017-08-03 |access-date=2019-03-19 }}</ref><ref name="jewishgen.org">{{cite web |url=https://www.jewishgen.org/databases/Belarus/brest.htm|work=The Brest Ghetto Passport Archive |title=Monument at Bronnaya Gora |publisher=JewishGen |year=2014 |first1=John |last1=Garrard |first2=Carol |last2=Garrard|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201031105/https://www.jewishgen.org/databases/Belarus/brest.htm |archivedate=December 1, 2017 }}</ref><ref name="cemeteryproject">{{cite web |url=http://www.iajgsjewishcemeteryproject.org/belarus/antopol.html |title=Antopal: Brest. The Antopol Ghetto |work=The ghetto liquidation 'Aktion' |quote=Deportations to Bronna Gora lasted four days beginning October 15, 1942 |publisher=International Jewish Cemetery Project, with links to resources |accessdate=November 26, 2017 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804113242/http://www.iajgsjewishcemeteryproject.org/belarus/antopol.html |archivedate=August 4, 2017 }}</ref>在前[[沃倫省|沃倫省]]的[[羅夫諾|羅夫諾]]郊区的{{le|索森斯基|Sosenki}}森林中，有超过23,000名犹太人男女老幼被枪杀。<ref>{{citation |title=Holocaust in Rovno: The Massacre at Sosenki Forest, November 1941 |first=Jeffrey |last=Burds |publisher=Northeastern University. Sponsored by the YIVO Institute of Jewish Research, New York |url=http://www.jewishgen.org/Yizkor/rovno2/files/Rovno_Burds.pdf |at=p. 2 (19 of 151 in current document)|isbn=9781137388391 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803215817/http://www.jewishgen.org/Yizkor/rovno2/files/Rovno_Burds.pdf |archivedate=August 3, 2017 }}.</ref>在波翁卡村（Górka Połonka）的森林（见地图），25,000名犹太人被迫脱光衣服，然后躺在其他人的尸体上被成批处决；其中大多数受害者来自{{tsl|en|Łuck Ghetto|卢茨克隔都}}。<ref>{{citation |title=Połonka Mount, place of executions and the Holocaust mass grave |trans-title=Górka-Połonka – miejsce egzekucji i zbiorowy grób ofiar Zagłady |publisher=[[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|POLIN Museum of the History of Polish Jews]] |url=http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/luck/13,sites-of-martyrdom/45483,gorka-polonka-miejsce-egzekucji-i-zbiorowy-grob-ofiar-zaglady/ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804012451/http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/luck/13,sites-of-martyrdom/45483,gorka-polonka-miejsce-egzekucji-i-zbiorowy-grob-ofiar-zaglady/ |archivedate=2017-08-04 |access-date=2019-03-19 }}</ref><ref name="Polonka">Yad Vashem, {{YouTube |id=Q87bYVp0EGA |title=Mass-murder of Łuck Jews at Gurka Polonka in August 1942}} 注：波翁卡村（{{lang-pl|Górka Połonka}}）以及它下辖的波翁卡丘（[http://wolyn.ovh.org/opisy/gorka_polonka-07.html Połonka Little Hill]{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720074205/http://www.wolyn.ovh.org/opisy/gorka_polonka-07.html |date=July 20, 2008 }}）在纪录片中的拼写是错误的。该片有幸存者{{tsl|en|Shmuel Shilo|什穆尔·希洛}}的证词。</ref>[[利沃夫隔都|利沃夫隔都]]囚犯的处决地点安排在{{tsl|en|Janowska concentration camp|亚诺夫斯卡集中营|亚诺夫斯卡}}附近，有35,000-40,000名犹太人被杀害后埋葬在皮亚斯基（Piaski）峡谷。<ref name=Kerenji>{{cite book |title=The Holocaust in the East: Local Perpetrators and Soviet Responses |authors=Marina Sorokina, Tarik Cyril Amar |series=Pitt Series in Russian and East European Studies |isbn=978-0-8229-6293-9 |url=http://filercosmin.com/books/download/asin=0822962934&type=full |year=2014 |publisher=University of Pittsburgh Press |pages=124, 165, 172, 255 |via=direct download 13.6 MB |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171014034941/http://filercosmin.com/books/download/asin%3D0822962934%26type%3Dfull |archivedate=2017-10-14 |access-date=2019-03-19 }} 另见： {{cite book |title=Jewish Responses to Persecution: 1942–1943 |first=Emil |last=Kerenji |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gXDYBAAAQBAJ&q=Janowska+100%2C000+DAW |year=2014 |isbn=978-1442236271 |pages=69–70, 539 }}</ref>

秩序警察对[[德占波兰的犹太隔都|占领区的犹太隔都]]实施了清场，将囚犯装入屠杀列车，并射杀无法转移或企图逃离的人。{{tsl|en|collaborationist auxiliary police|协同辅助警察}}通过在隔都实施大规模屠杀的方式，对犹太人民施加恐怖。<ref name="Browning">{{cite book |title=Arrival in Poland |last=Browning |first=Christopher |year=1998 |url=http://hampshirehigh.com/exchange2012/docs/BROWNING-Ordinary%20Men.%20Reserve%20Police%20Battalion%20101%20and%20the%20Final%20Solution%20in%20Poland%20(1992).pdf |orig-year=1992 |publisher=Penguin Books |work=Ordinary Men: Reserve Police Battalion 101 and the Final Solution in Poland |pages=52, 77, 79, 80, 135 |id=PDF file, direct download 7.91 MB complete |quote=''Also:''[https://www.webcitation.org/6GIJ2XpOy?url=http://hampshirehigh.com/exchange2012/docs/BROWNING-Ordinary%20Men.%20Reserve%20Police%20Battalion%20101%20and%20the%20Final%20Solution%20in%20Poland%20(1992).pdf PDF cache archived by WebCite.] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010164107/http://hampshirehigh.com/exchange2012/docs/BROWNING-Ordinary%20Men.%20Reserve%20Police%20Battalion%20101%20and%20the%20Final%20Solution%20in%20Poland%20(1992).pdf |archivedate=October 10, 2014 }}</ref><ref name="ARC">{{cite web |url=http://www.deathcamps.org/occupation/erntefest.html |title=Erntefest |publisher=ARC |work=Occupation of the East |year=2004 |accessdate=2013-04-26 |author=ARC |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130118102221/http://www.deathcamps.org/occupation/erntefest.html |archivedate=January 18, 2013}}</ref>他们被部署在莱因哈德行动的所有主要杀戮地点​​：施加恐怖是党卫队训练他们的主要目的。{{r|B&G30}}来自乌克兰的[[特拉夫尼基人|特拉夫尼基人]]部队在贝乌热茨、索比布尔、特雷布林卡二号营的犹太人灭绝行动中行动活跃；他们还在[[華沙猶太區起義|华沙]]（三次参与，见{{tsl|en|Stroop Report|施特鲁普报告}}）、[[琴斯托霍瓦隔都|琴斯托霍瓦]]、[[卢布林隔都|卢布林]]、[[利沃夫隔都|利沃夫]]、{{tsl|en|Radom Ghetto|拉多姆隔都|拉多姆}}、[[克拉科夫猶太人區|克拉科夫]]、[[比亚韦斯托克隔都|比亚韦斯托克]]（两次）、[[马伊达内克集中营|马伊达内克]]、[[奥斯威辛集中营|奥斯维辛]]、[[特拉夫尼基集中营|特拉夫尼基]]、{{r|USHMM1}}{{tsl|en|Łomazy|沃玛茨}}、[[缅济热茨|缅济热茨]]、[[武庫夫|武庫夫]]、[[波德拉謝地區拉曾|拉曾]]、[[帕爾切夫|帕爾切夫]]、[[孔斯科沃拉|孔斯科沃拉]]、{{tsl|en|Komarówka, Lublin Voivodeship|科马鲁夫卡（卢布林省）|科马鲁夫卡}}等地，以及卢布林/马伊达内克集中营的其余分区（包括{{tsl|en|Poniatowa concentration camp|波尼亚托瓦集中营|波尼亚托瓦}}、[[克拉希尼克|克拉希尼克]]、[[普瓦維|普瓦維]]）实施大屠杀。特拉夫尼基人的行动得到了党卫队、[[黨衛隊保安處|黨衛隊保安處]]、{{tsl|en|Kriminalpolizei|刑事警察(纳粹德国)|刑事警察}}以及[[秩序警察|秩序警察]][[第101后备警察营|后备警察营]]的支援（每支部队都对数千名犹太人的消灭负责）。{{r|EC55}}犹太人的大规模处决（如在[[舍布涅集中营|舍布涅]]的情况）是{{tsl|en|SS-Truppenübungsplatz Heidelager|党卫队海德拉格训练场}}<ref>位于波兰东南的{{tsl|en|Pustków, Podkarpackie Voivodeship|普什库夫（喀尔巴阡山省）|普什库夫}}</ref>的[[党卫队第14武装掷弹兵师|乌克兰武装党卫队师]]士兵常规训练的一部分。<ref name="Heidelager">{{cite web |url=http://pustkow.republika.pl/historia.html |title=HL-Heidelager: SS-TruppenÜbungsPlatz |author=Mirek Kusibab |publisher=Pustkow.Republika.pl |id=Historia poligonu Heidelager w Pustkowie |year=2013 |work=History of the Range with photographs |language=pl |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418040914/http://pustkow.republika.pl/historia.html |archivedate=April 18, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Goldsworthy">{{cite book |title=Valhalla's Warriors |url=https://books.google.com/?id=1KPsZGCesO0C&pg=PA144&lpg=PA144&dq=Szebnie+%22POW%22#v=onepage&q=Szebnie%20%22POW%22&f=false |publisher=Dog Ear Publishing |work=A History of the Waffen-SS on the Eastern Front 1941–1945 |year=2010 |author=Terry Goldsworthy |page=144 |via=Google Book preview |isbn=978-1-60844-639-1}}</ref>在东北部，{{tsl|en|Oskar Dirlewanger|奥斯卡·迪尔勒万格}}的“{{tsl|en|36th Waffen Grenadier Division of the SS|党卫队第36武装掷弹兵师|偷猎者旅}}”在{{tsl|en|Belarusian Auxiliary Police|白俄罗斯辅警}}的帮助下，在杀戮行动中训练{{tsl|en|Belarusian Home Defence|白俄罗斯国土卫队}}。<ref name="Wilson113">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jZJntMQtkSYC&q=%28BKA%29 |title=Belarus: The Last European Dictatorship |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2011 |accessdate=6 February 2015 |last=Wilson |first=Andrew |pages=109, 110, 113 |isbn=978-0-300-13435-3 |ref=harv}}</ref>截至1945年5月[[第二次世界大戰歐洲戰場的結束|第二次世界大战欧洲战场结束]]时，已有超过90％的波兰犹太人丧生。{{r|Lukas1989}}

===海乌姆诺灭绝营===
{{detail|海乌姆诺灭绝营|{{tsl|en|Chełmno Trials|海乌姆诺审判}}}}
[[File:Chełmno_(Kulmhof)_1942_(Koło).jpg|thumb]]的犹太人被迫在路上抛弃自己的行李。图中的犹太人来自[[羅茲猶太區|罗兹隔都]]]]
[[海乌姆诺灭绝营|海乌姆诺灭绝营]]建于希特勒发动[[巴巴羅薩行動|巴巴羅薩行動]]之后，是纳粹建造的第一座[[灭绝营|灭绝营]]。该集中营是开发其他灭绝场所的试点项目。纳粹先前在[[索尔达乌集中营|索尔达乌]]以毒气杀害了1,500名波兰人，完成了以毒气处决的相关实验。<ref name="soldau">{{citation |author=The Simon Wiesenthal Center |year=1997 |chapter-url=http://motlc.wiesenthal.com/site/pp.asp?c=gvKVLcMVIuG&b=394667 |title=Responses to Revisionist Arguments |chapter=Part 5 |publisher=Museum of Tolerance. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170403232419/http://motlc.wiesenthal.com/site/pp.asp?c=gvKVLcMVIuG&b=394667 |archivedate=2017-04-03 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}另见：{{citation |author={{tsl|en|Henry Friedlander||Henry Friedlander}} |year=1995 |url=http://www.lbihs.at/FriedlanderFromEuthanasia.pdf |title=From Euthanasia to the Final Solution |at=pp. 18–21 in current copy |publisher=LBIHS |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418234913/http://www.lbihs.at/FriedlanderFromEuthanasia.pdf |archivedate=April 18, 2015 }}; {{citation |author=International Tracing Service ''Catalogue'' |origyear=1949 |url=http://www.warrelics.eu/forum/konzentrationslagers/brief-chronology-konzentrationslager-system-356265/ |title=Brief Chronology Of the Konzentrationslager System |publisher=War Relics |year=2013 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728235135/http://www.warrelics.eu/forum/konzentrationslagers/brief-chronology-konzentrationslager-system-356265/ |archivedate=July 28, 2014 }}</ref>海乌姆诺的杀戮方法源于[[T-4行动|“安乐死”计划]]；该计划中，大量不知情的医院病人在{{tsl|en|Bernburg Euthanasia Centre|伯恩堡安乐死中心|伯恩堡}}、{{tsl|en|Hadamar Euthanasia Centre|哈达玛尔安乐死中心|哈达玛尔}}与{{tsl|en|Sonnenstein Euthanasia Centre|索能斯坦安乐死中心|索能斯坦}}的气密淋浴房中被毒气杀死。<ref>{{harvp|Browning|2004|pp=191–192|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=d9Wg4gjtP3cC&q=Sonnenstein+chambers"Adult euthanasia."]}}</ref>距[[罗兹_(波兰)|罗兹]]50公里的海乌姆诺的杀戮场地包括一处类似于索能斯坦的被腾退的庄园，用于脱衣，其后面有卡车装载坡道。海乌姆诺西北4公里处有一处大型森林空地，被用于大规模埋葬以及一段时间后引入的露天火化。<ref name="Montague-1">{{citation |last=Montague |first=Patrick |year=2012 |title=Chełmno and the Holocaust: The History of Hitler's First Death Camp |publisher={{tsl|en|University of North Carolina Press||University of North Carolina Press}} |location=Chapel Hill |url=https://books.google.com/?id=02ABWyc_Ks0C&pg=PA151&lpg=PA151&dq=Walter+Piller,+Hermann+Gielow,+SS-Sonderkommando+Kulmhof#v=onepage&q=Walter%20Piller%2C%20Hermann%20Gielow%2C%20SS-Sonderkommando%20Kulmhof&f=false |isbn=978-0-8078-3527-2 |via=Google Books}}</ref>

所有来自[[瓦尔特兰帝国大区|瓦尔特兰帝国大区]]的{{tsl|en|Judenfrei|去犹太化}}区域的犹太人都被以“重新安置”的名义发配到海乌姆诺。至少有14.5万名来自[[羅茲猶太區|罗兹隔都]]的囚犯在1942年至1944年间的几次驱逐行动中丧生于海乌姆诺。<ref>{{cite web |year=2015 |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia – The Jews of Lodz|publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |url=http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005071 |accessdate=12 April 2015 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150419003302/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005071 |archivedate=April 19, 2015 }}</ref><ref name="lodz-ghetto">{{cite book |url=http://www.lodz-ghetto.com/introduction.html,1 |title=Litzmannstadt Ghetto, Lodz |publisher=Litzmannstadt Ghetto homepage|work=Traces of the Litzmannstadt Getto. A Guide to the Past: Introduction |date=2015 |accessdate=12 April 2015 |author=Michal Latosinski |isbn=978-83-7415-000-2|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223102917/http://www.lodz-ghetto.com/introduction.html,1 |archivedate=December 23, 2017 }}</ref>此外，还有2万名外国犹太人和5,000名罗姆人从德国、奥地利和捷克斯洛伐克被带入。<ref name="kehilalinks.jewishgen">{{cite web |url=http://kehilalinks.jewishgen.org/lodz/statistics.htm |title=Lodz Ghetto Deportations and Statistics |publisher=Łódź ShtetLinks · JewishGen |work=Sources: Encyclopedia of the Holocaust, Baranowski, Dobroszycki, Wiesenthal, Yad Vashem Timeline |date=2007 |accessdate=12 April 2015 |author=Shirley Rotbein Flaum, Roni Seibel Liebowitz |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321021602/http://kehilalinks.jewishgen.org/lodz/statistics.htm |archivedate=2015-03-21 }}</ref>所有受害者都被移动式{{tsl|en|gas van|毒气车}}（Sonderwagen）杀死：车上的排气管经过重新配置，汽油中添加毒药。在灭绝营存在的最后阶段，尸体被挖掘出来并在{{tsl|en|Sonderaktion 1005|1005特别行动}}期间露天火化了几周。骨灰与碎骨混合在一起，装在用床单制成的口袋中，每晚用卡车运倒入附近的[[瓦尔塔河|瓦尔塔河]]，从而去除大屠杀的证据。<ref name="JTA">{{cite web |url=http://www.jta.org/1963/01/22/archive/jewish-survivors-of-chelmno-camp-testify-at-trial-of-guards |title=Jewish Survivors of Chelmno Camp Testify at Trial of Guards |publisher=Jewish Telegraphic Agency |work=Internet Archive |date=January 22, 1963 |accessdate=2013-06-14 |author=JTA|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140220122211/http://www.jta.org/1963/01/22/archive/jewish-survivors-of-chelmno-camp-testify-at-trial-of-guards|archivedate=February 20, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Lichtenstein">{{cite web |url=http://www.fluchschrift.net/verbrech/november/011141.htm |title=01.11.1941. Errichtung des ersten Vernichtungslagers in Chelmno |publisher=Fluchschrift – Deutsche Verbrechen |work=Heiner Lichtenstein, Daten aus der Zeitgeschichte, in: Tribüne Nr. 179/2006|year=2013 |accessdate=2013-06-14 |author=Fluchschrift |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517003801/http://www.fluchschrift.net/verbrech/november/011141.htm |archivedate=May 17, 2012 }}</ref>

===奥斯维辛-比克瑙===
{{detail|奥斯维辛集中营}}
[[File:Birkenau_Inmates_heading_towards_the_barracks_in_the_camp.jpg|thumb]]关押的囚犯]]

[[奥斯威辛集中营|奥斯威辛集中营]]是德国纳粹建造的最大的灭绝中心，位于[[克拉科夫|克拉科夫]]以西64公里处。<ref>{{citation |title=Auschwitz: The Nazi Solution |author=Andrew Rawson |publisher=Pen and Sword |year=2015 |page=121 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hTagBwAAQBAJ&q=Auschwitz+forty+miles |isbn=978-1473827981 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819115843/https://books.google.com/books?id=hTagBwAAQBAJ&q=Auschwitz+forty+miles |dead-url=no }}</ref>奥斯威辛平均每天处理1.5列[[大屠杀列车|大屠杀列车]]。<ref name="Enghelberg63">{{cite book |url=https://www.amazon.com/HOLOCAUST-transport-companies-agreement-operation-ebook/dp/B004C44N58/ref=sr_1_10?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1391784099&sr=1-10#reader_B004C44N58 |title=The trains of the Holocaust |publisher=Kindle Edition |author=Hedi Enghelberg |year=2013 |page=63 |isbn=978-1-60585-123-5 |quote=[http://www.enghelberg.com/EDICIONES/trains_holocaust.htm Book excerpts] from Enghelberg.com.}}</ref>绝大多数被遣送至奥斯维辛的囚犯在抵达后数小时内便被杀害。<ref name="auschwitz.org/jews">{{cite web |url=http://auschwitz.org/en/history/categories-of-prisoners/jews-in-auschwitz/auschwitz-as-a-center-for-the-extermination-of-the-jews |title=Auschwitz as a center for the extermination of the Jews |publisher=Auschwitz-Birkenau Memorial and State Museum|work=Jews in Auschwitz |date=2015 |accessdate=13 April 2015 |author=Memorial and Museum |quote=Countries of origin, Selection in the camp, Treatment. |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320095238/http://auschwitz.org/en/history/categories-of-prisoners/jews-in-auschwitz/auschwitz-as-a-center-for-the-extermination-of-the-jews |archivedate=March 20, 2016 }}</ref>集中营于1942年3月安装了第一个永久性[[毒气室|毒气室]]。使用[[齊克隆B|齊克隆B]]为杀人毒剂的犹太人灭绝于7月开始。{{r|Fritsch}}1943年，纳粹在比克瑙建造了四组杀戮装置，每组装置包括更衣室、多个毒气室和[[火葬|工业规模的焚尸炉]]）。<ref name="gascamp">{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/gascamp.html |title=Gassing Victims in the Holocaust: Background & Overview |publisher=Jewish Virtual Library|work=Extermination camps in occupied Poland |author=Institut Fuer Zeitgeschicthe (Institute for Contemporary History) |year=1992 |location=Munich, Germany |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150529061418/http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/gascamp.html |archivedate=May 29, 2015 }}</ref>到1943年底，比克瑙这座杀戮工厂已经拥有了四座所谓的“碉堡”，共计十几个毒气室；杀戮装置昼夜不停地运行。<ref>{{citation |title=The Fallacy of Race and the Shoah |authors=Naomi Kramer, Ronald Headland |page=254 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sg6pDAAAQBAJ&q=Killing+facilities+extended |publisher=University of Ottawa Press |year=1998 |isbn=978-0776617121 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819215151/https://books.google.com/books?id=sg6pDAAAQBAJ&q=Killing+facilities+extended |dead-url=no }} 另见： {{citation |title=The Destruction of the European Jews |author=Raul Hilberg |pages=948–949 |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2003 |isbn=978-0300095920 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HinIpmliz2MC&q=barely+175%2C000+Jews |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819114731/https://books.google.com/books?id=HinIpmliz2MC&q=barely+175%2C000+Jews |dead-url=no }}</ref>经过犹太人站台（Judenrampe）上无情的“选择过程”之后，每天有多达6,000人被毒气杀害并火化。<ref>{{cite web |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia –Gassing Operations |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |url=http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005220 |accessdate=15 June 2015 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208103605/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005220 |archivedate=February 8, 2015 }}</ref>{{r|AuschwitzEng}}帝国安全总办（[[党卫队国家安全部|RSHA]]）组织的运输中，只有大约10％的被驱逐者得到登记并分配到比克瑙的营房。<ref name="AuschwitzEng">{{cite web |url=http://www.jewishgen.org/ForgottenCamps/Camps/AuschwitzEng.html |title=Auschwitz-Birkenau Death Factory|publisher=The Forgotten Camps |date=2006 |accessdate=13 April 2015 |author=Vincent Châtel & Chuck Ferree |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403092308/http://www.jewishgen.org/ForgottenCamps/Camps/AuschwitzEng.html |archivedate=April 3, 2015 }}</ref>

奥斯威辛II号营的灭绝计划导致130万至150万人死亡。<ref name="piper/museum">{{cite web |url=http://auschwitz.org/en/history/the-number-of-victims/number-of-deportees-by-ethnicity |title=Number of deportees by ethnicity |publisher=Auschwitz-Birkenau Memorial and State Museum |work=Ilu ludzi zginęło w KL Auschwitz. Liczba ofiar w świetle źródeł i badań, Oświęcim 1992, tables 14–27 |date=2015 |accessdate=14 April 2015 |author={{tsl|en|Franciszek Piper||Franciszek Piper}} |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919192817/http://auschwitz.org/en/history/the-number-of-victims/number-of-deportees-by-ethnicity |archivedate=September 19, 2016 }}</ref> 其中超过110万是来自欧洲各地的犹太人，包括20万名儿童。{{r|auschwitz.org/jews}}{{r|auschwitz}}有40万名受害者得到了登记，不到奥斯威辛到达总人数的三分之一；这40万人中有14万-15万名非犹太波兰人、2.3万名吉普赛人，1.5万名苏联战俘和2.5万其他受害者。{{r|piper/museum}}<ref name="faq">{{cite report |title=How many people were registered as prisoners in Auschwitz? |publisher=Auschwitz-Birkenau Memorial and Museum|url=http://auschwitz.org/en/museum/auschwitz-prisoners/faq |work=History of KL Auschwitz |section=The Number and Origins of the Victims |year=2015|sectionurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030420205757/http://www.auschwitz-muzeum.oswiecim.pl/html/eng/historia_KL/liczba_narodowosc_ofiar_ok.html |author=Auschwitz-Birkenau Foundation |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150802041145/http://auschwitz.org/en/museum/auschwitz-prisoners/faq |archivedate=August 2, 2015}}</ref>奥斯威辛从德占波兰得到了大约30万犹太人，<ref>{{citation |title=Bloodlands: Europe Between Hitler and Stalin|author=Timothy Snyder |publisher=Basic Books |year=2012 |isbn=978-0465032976 |page=314 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=maEfAQAAQBAJ&q=about+300%2C000+Polish|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=maEfAQAAQBAJ&q=about+300%2C000+Polish |archivedate=July 5, 2018}}</ref>他们是从中转营和被清场的隔都用[[大屠殺列車|货运列车]]运来的。{{r|auschwitz2}}向奥斯维辛的运输从{{tsl|en|Beuthen Ghetto|比托姆隔都|比托姆}}开始（1942年2月15日）、随后是[[奧爾庫什|奧爾庫什]]（6月中的三天）、[[奧特沃茨克|奧特沃茨克]]（在8月）、{{tsl|en|Łomża Ghetto|沃姆扎隔都|沃姆扎}}和[[切哈努夫|切哈努夫]]（11月），<ref>{{citation |title=The Scrolls of Auschwitz |authors=Ber Mark, Isaiah Avrech |publisher=Am Oved |year=1985 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WjlnAAAAMAAJ&dq=Ciechanow |pages=71, 260 |id=Hometown of{{tsl|en|Roza Robota||Róża (Roza) Robota}}. |isbn=9789651302527 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820011022/https://books.google.com/books?id=WjlnAAAAMAAJ&dq=Ciechanow |dead-url=no }}</ref>然后是[[克拉科夫猶太人區|克拉科夫]]（1943年3月13日）、{{r|Gutman232}} [[索斯诺维茨隔都|索斯诺维茨]]、[[本津隔都|本津]]、[[栋布罗瓦古尔尼恰|栋布罗瓦]]（1943年6月至8月），{{r|jewishgen}}以及其他几十个大都市和城镇，<ref name="statistics">统计数据所用的资料包括[[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|波蘭猶太人歷史博物館]]{{tsl|en|Virtual Shtetl|虚拟犹太镇}}的[http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/selectcity/  "Glossary of 2,077 Jewish towns in Poland"]{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208215116/http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/selectcity/ |date=February 8, 2016 }}、以及[https://web.archive.org/web/20141015055255/http://www.izrael.badacz.org/historia/szoa_getto.html  Gedeon 的 "Getta Żydowskie"]，以及[https://web.archive.org/web/20141214124022/http://www.deathcamps.org/occupation/ghettolist.htm Michael Peters 的 "Ghetto List"]. 2015年3月14日查阅。</ref>1944年8月，德占波兰境内最后一个隔都——[[羅茲猶太區|罗兹隔都]]遭到清场，居民同样被遣送至奥斯维辛。{{r|jewishvirtuallibrary3}}奥斯维辛-比克瑙集中营的毒气室和焚尸炉于1944年11月25日根据海因里希·希姆莱的命令被炸毁；纳粹企图以这种方式摧毁大规模杀戮的证据。{{r|USHMM4}}

===特雷布林卡===
{{detail|特雷布林卡灭绝营}}
[[File:Treblinka_uprising_(Ząbecki_1943).jpg|thumb]]在囚犯起义期间熊熊燃烧。起义中集中营的营房和储油罐被点燃。 来自{{tsl|en|Franciszek Ząbecki|弗兰西舍克·赞别斯基}}的秘密照片]]

[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡灭绝营]]专为杀人而设计和建造，是保存至今的三个此类设施之一——另外两个是[[贝乌热茨灭绝营|贝乌热茨]]和[[索比布尔灭绝营|索比布尔]]。<ref>{{harvp|Browning|2004|p=374|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=d9Wg4gjtP3cC&q=secret+camps+designed+perpetrate+mass+murder camps designed to perpetrate mass murder.]}}</ref>所有的这类杀人设施都位于远离人口中心的树木繁茂的地区，并通过[[铁路支线|铁路支线]]与波兰铁路系统相连。设施中有可调动的党卫队工作人员。<ref name="Arad1999">{{cite book |title=Belzec, Sobibor, Treblinka: The Operation Reinhard Death Camps|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YglnAAAAMAAJ |pages=152–153 |first=Yitzhak |last=Arad |publisher=Indiana University Press |year=1999|orig-year=1987 |isbn=978-0-253-21305-1 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=YglnAAAAMAAJ|archivedate=July 5, 2018 }}</ref>在铁轨旁边有一座铁路站台，周围是2.5米高的铁丝网围栏。营区中建造了大型营房，用于存放下车的受害者的财物。其中一座营房伪装成一座火车站，甚至配有假木钟和标牌，以防止新来的人意识到自己面临的命运。{{r|Yeger}}通向毒气室的道路被称作“天堂之路”，用围栏封锁，沿途设有收银台用于收集护照和钱币，以便“妥善保管”。毒气室被伪装成公共淋浴间，背后是用挖掘机挖掘出的埋葬坑。<ref name="Smith103">{{Cite book |ref=harv |last=Smith |first=Mark S. |title=Treblinka Survivor: The Life and Death of Hershl Sperling |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HBc7AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=Himmelstrasse&f=false |publisher=The History Press |year=2010 |isbn=978-0-7524-5618-8 |via=Google Books preview |pages=103–107 |quote=''See Smith's book excerpts at:'' [http://www.holocaustresearchproject.org/survivor/sperling.html Hershl Sperling: Personal Testimony] by David Adams, and the book summary at [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1302964/Last-victim-Treblinka-He-survived-SEVEN-Nazi-concentration-camps--nightmare-caught-him.html Last victim of Treblinka] by Tony Rennell. |accessdate=9 April 2015 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017123029/https://books.google.com/books?id=HBc7AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=Himmelstrasse&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>

特雷布林卡灭绝营位于[[华沙|华沙]]东北部80千米，{{r|treblinka}}经过被逐出德国的劳改犯三个月的[[第二次世界大战时期德国统治下的强制劳役|强制劳动建设]]后，于1942年7月24日开始运作。<ref>Kopówka & Rytel-Andrianik (2011), chapt. 3:1, p. 77.</ref>从[[华沙|波兰首都]]运出犹太人的计划（“{{tsl|en|Grossaktion Warsaw (1942)|华沙大行动}}”）的计划随即立刻开始。{{r|YV}}{{r|BE-B}}{{r|BE-B2}}1942年夏季中的两个月里，约有25.4万名[[華沙猶太區|华沙隔都]]囚犯在特雷布林卡被消灭（一说至少有30万人）。{{r|USHMM_War}}犹太人抵达特雷布林卡后立即被迫脱光衣服；他们随后以200人为一批关入双层毒气室，使用坦克引擎产生的废气处决。男人最先被处决，随后是妇女和儿童。<ref name="JVL-Reinhard5">{{cite web|url=https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/reinhard.html#5 |title=The Construction of the Treblinka Extermination Camp |publisher=Jewish Virtual Library.org |work=Yad Vashem Studies, XVI |year=1984 |accessdate=3 November 2013 |author=McVay, Kenneth |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905055409/http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/reinhard.html#5 |archivedate=September 5, 2015 }}</ref>{{r|urteilsbegr}}{{r|nizkor}}1942年8月至9月期间，毒气室以砖块重建并加以扩建，能够每天杀死12,000至15,000名受害者，<ref name="Ainsztein">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=L-1mAAAAMAAJ&dq=Treblinka+maximum+gassing+capacity&q=%22Treblinka+25%2C000%22 |title=Jewish Resistance in Nazi-Occupied Eastern Europe |publisher=University of Michigan (reprint) |origyear=1974 |year=2008 |accessdate=21 December 2013 |author=Ainsztein, Reuben|page=917 |isbn=978-0-236-15490-6 |via=Google Books snipet view |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503040505/https://books.google.com/books?ei=XWW2UrfyGNjtoASaw4HgDA&id=L-1mAAAAMAAJ&dq=Treblinka+maximum+gassing+capacity&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22Treblinka+25,000%22 |archivedate=May 3, 2016 }}</ref>最多可在24小时内处死22,000人。{{r|Sumler}}死者最初被埋在大型乱葬坑中，但腐烂尸体的恶臭在十公里以外都能闻到。{{r|DC278}}纳粹因此开始在由混凝土柱子和铁轨组成的露天烤架上焚烧尸体。{{r|perpetrators}}特雷布林卡运行的一年内在营中遇害的人数从80万到120万不等，确切数据不明。{{r|Kopówka}}{{r|generalgouvernement1}}1943年10月19日，在[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡囚犯起义]]后不久，该营地被{{tsl|en|Odilo Globocnik|奥迪洛·格洛博奇尼克}}关闭，{{r|indianapolis}}莱茵哈德行动此时已几乎完成。<ref name="Kopówka">{{harvp|Kopówka|Rytel-Andrianik|2011|loc=[http://www.polacyizydzi.com/dam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf pp. 76–102 (of 610) in PDF.]}}[https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1] {{Wayback|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.polacyizydzi.com%2Fdam-im-imie-na-wieki.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 |date=20190922064520 }}</ref>

===贝乌热茨===
{{detail|贝乌热茨灭绝营}}
[[File:Belzec_-_SS_staff_(1942).jpg|thumb]]的[[骷髅总队|骷髅总队]]]]

[[贝乌热茨灭绝营|贝乌热茨灭绝营]]位于{{tsl|en|Lublin Reservation|卢布林保留地|卢布林区}}贝乌热茨火车站附近，于1942年3月17日开始正式运作。灭绝营起初有三座临时搭建的毒气室；后来被六座由砖石和灰泥建造的毒气室取代，使该设施能够一次处理超过1,000名受害者。{{r|bay/kola}}至少有434,500名犹太人在贝乌热茨遇害。然而，由于该灭绝营缺乏可以核实的幸存者，因此它相对较为不出名。{{r|USHMM_Belzec}}死者尸体埋葬在乱葬坑中，由于{{tsl|en|putrefaction|腐烂}}而在高温下膨胀，使得土地开裂；贝乌热茨于1942年10月引入焚尸坑后解决了这个问题。{{r|brezezinka}}

[[武装党卫队|武装党卫队]]的{{tsl|en|Kurt Gerstein|库尔特·戈尔施泰因}}在大屠杀期间负责从{{tsl|en|Degesch|德意志害虫防治公司}}供应[[齊克隆B|齊克隆B]]。<ref name="Y357">{{cite book |title=The Holocaust: The fate of European Jewry, 1932–1945 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=e_aRvKpLUf0C&pg=PA351#v=onepage&q=Kurt%20Gerstein&f=false |year=1991 |publisher=Oxford University Press|pages=356–357 |isbn=978-0-19-504523-9 |last1=Yahil |first1=Leni |last2=Friedman |first2=Ina |last3=Galai |first3=Hayah |accessdate=2015-04-15}}</ref>他在战后递交给[[同盟國_(第二次世界大戰)|盟军]]的《{{tsl|en|Gerstein Report|戈尔施泰因报告}}》中写道，1942年8月17日他在贝乌热茨目睹了45辆货车到达灭绝营，车上的6,700名囚犯中有1,450人已经死亡。{{r|Gerstein}}那列火车上的犹太人来自距离灭绝营不到一百公里的[[利沃夫隔都|利沃夫隔都]]。{{r|Gerstein}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia – Belzec: Chronology |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum|url=http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10007206 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150420082849/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10007206 |archivedate=April 20, 2015 }}</ref>贝乌热茨的最后一批犹太人于1942年12月抵达灭绝营。{{r|Belzec, Sobibor, Treblinka: The Operation Reinhard Death Camps}}将挖掘出来的尸体烧毁的过程一直持续到次年3月。<ref name="arc-belzec">{{cite web |author=ARC contributing authors |title=Belzec Camp History|publisher=Aktion Reinhard Camps |url=http://www.deathcamps.org/belzec/belzec.html |date=26 August 2006 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051225034440/http://www.deathcamps.org/belzec/belzec.html |archivedate=December 25, 2005 }}</ref>其余500名{{tsl|en|Sonderkommando|特别支队}}囚犯见证了灭绝过程，拆除了营地，{{r|USHMM_Belzec}}随后在接下来的几个月里在附近的[[索比布尔集中营|索比布尔集中营]]遭到处决。{{r|archeologists}}{{r|jewishgen6}}

===索比布尔===
{{detail|索比布尔集中营}}
[[File:Hoefletelegram.jpg|thumb]]运送至[[索比布尔集中营|索比布尔集中营]]]]

[[索比布尔集中营|索比布尔集中营]]被伪装成离[[卢布林|卢布林]]不远的铁路中转营，于1942年5月开始大规模毒气处决。{{r|destruction}}与其他灭绝中心一样，从清场的隔都和过境营地（{{tsl|en|Izbica concentration camp|伊兹比察集中营|伊兹比察}}和[[孔斯科沃拉|孔斯科沃拉]]）经大屠杀列车运来的犹太人会遇到一名穿着医用外套的党卫队队员。在索比布尔，[[親衛隊上級小隊領袖|党卫队二级小队长]]赫尔曼·米歇尔（Hermann Michel）命令囚犯接受“消毒”。<ref>{{harvp|Schelvis|2014|p=70 |loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=OB1nAwAAQBAJ&q=Hermann+Michel Arrival and Selection.]}}</ref>

新来的人被强制分成小组，交出他们的贵重物品，并在一座由院墙包围的院子里洗澡；特别支队的理发师负责剪掉女人的头发。脱掉衣服后，犹太人就被带到一条狭窄的小路上，进入伪装成淋浴间的毒气室。纳粹使用从红军坦克中取出的汽油发动机产生毒气，由排气管释放出一氧化碳气体。.<ref name="project.org">{{cite web|url=http://www.holocaustresearchproject.org/ar/arperpsspeak.html |title=Former Members of the SS-Sonderkommando Sobibor describe their experiences in the Sobibor death camp in their own words |publisher=H.E.A.R.T |work=Belzec, Sobibor & Treblinka Death Camps |date=2007 |accessdate=16 April 2015 |author=Chris Webb, C.L. |quote=It was a heavy Russian benzine engine – presumably a tank or tractor motor at least 200 horsepower V-motor, 8 cylinders, water cooled (''SS-Scharführer'' {{tsl|en|Erich Fuchs||Erich Fuchs}}).|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110906021944/http://www.holocaustresearchproject.org/ar/arperpsspeak.html |archivedate=September 6, 2011 }}</ref>受害者的尸体被取出毒气室，放在露天坑上的铁架上火化（纳粹使用了人体脂肪作为部分燃料）；遗骸被倾倒在七座“骨灰山”上。在索比布尔遇害的波兰犹太人总数估计至少为17万人。<ref name="Sobibór">{{harvp|Schelvis|2014|p=110}}.<br>{{space|2}}{{cite web|title=History of the Sobibór extermination camp |author=Sobibór branch of the {{tsl|en|Majdanek State Museum||Majdanek State Museum}} |year=2016 |url=http://www.sobibor-memorial.eu/en/history/history_of_the_camp/3# |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118214522/http://www.sobibor-memorial.eu/en/history/history_of_the_camp/3 |archivedate=January 18, 2017 }}<br>{{space|2}}{{cite web |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia – Sobibor|publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |url=https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005192 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529020902/https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005192 |archivedate=May 29, 2017 }}</ref>1943年10月14日，集中营发生了[[索比布尔集中营|囚犯起义]]，是仅有的两起成功的灭绝营犹太特别支队囚犯起义之一。300人在起义中逃亡，其中大多数被党卫队重新抓捕后处决。海因里希·希姆莱随即下令拆除集中营。{{r|schelvis}}{{r|holocaustresearchproject}}

===卢布林-马伊达内克===
{{detail|马伊达内克集中营}}
[[File:Lublin_-_Majdanek_-_014_-_Ovens.jpg|thumb]]

和索比布尔灭绝营一样，[[马伊达内克集中营|马伊达内克集中营]]同样位于卢布林郊区。集中营在{{tsl|en|epidemic typhus|斑疹伤寒疫情}}期间短暂关闭，于1942年3月为莱茵哈德行动重新开启。马伊达内克起初用于储存从贝乌热茨、索比布尔和特雷布林卡的受害者身上偷来的贵重物品，{{r|USHMM_LubMaj}}后来成为一个大量消灭波兰东南部犹太人口（如[[克拉科夫猶太人區|克拉科夫]]、[[利沃夫隔都|利沃夫]]、[[扎莫希奇|扎莫希奇]]、[[華沙猶太區|华沙]]）的灭绝营。1942年末，马伊达内克集中营中建造了毒气室。{{r|about}}{{pb}}波兰犹太人直接在其他囚犯的众目睽睽之下遭遇毒气处决，杀戮设施四周没有任何围栏。{{r|jewishvirtuallibrary7}}根据一位目击者的证词，“为了掩盖垂死者的哭喊，毒气室附近开着拖拉机引擎。”死者随后被带到火葬场。马伊达内克的7.9万名受害者中有5.9万波兰犹太人。{{r|Kranz}}{{r|Reszka}}1943年11月初，马伊达内克举行了“[[丰收节行动|丰收节行动]]”，是整个战争期间德国单次屠杀犹太人最多的一次行动。{{r|Browning}}行动结束后，集中营只剩下71名犹太人。{{r|WarCriminals:Nuremberg}}

==武装抵抗与隔都起义==
{{further|隔都起义|华沙隔都起义|{{tsl|en|Jewish resistance in German-occupied Europe|欧洲德占区的犹太抵抗运动}}|}}
[[File:Stroop_Report_-_Warsaw_Ghetto_Uprising_13.jpg|thumb]]期间被党卫队抓获的犹太妇女叛乱分子。]]

大众通常错误地认为大多数犹太人被动地接受死亡的命运；<ref name="Bauer2000">{{citation |title=An Interview With Prof. Yehuda Bauer |author=Yad Vashem|publisher=Shoah Resource Center, The International School for Holocaust Studies |year=2000 |at=pp. 28–30 of 58 in current document|url=http://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%203856.pdf |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090320161945/http://www1.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%203856.pdf |archivedate=March 20, 2009}}.</ref>然而这是彻头彻尾的谬误。{{r|Henry23}}犹太人对纳粹的抵抗不仅包括武装斗争，还包括精神上和文化上的抵抗；尽管隔都中的生活条件极不人道，但犹太人从精神抵抗中获得了尊严。{{r|Tot-Fein/Gersh}}<ref>{{citation |author={{tsl|en|Christopher Browning||Christopher Browning}} |title=Raul Hilberg |work=Yad Vashem Studies |publisher=Wallstein Verlag |year=2001 |pages=9–10 |issn=0084-3296 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pOWtjeac3mYC&q=Yehuda+Bauer+Unanswered |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819175115/https://books.google.com/books?id=pOWtjeac3mYC&q=Yehuda+Bauer+Unanswered |dead-url=no }}</ref>尽管长老们担忧反纳粹叛乱会招致对妇女和儿童的大规模报复，但犹太人中仍存在许多形式的抵抗。<ref name=Trunk>{{citation |title=Judenrat: The Jewish Councils in Eastern Europe Under Nazi Occupation |author={{tsl|en|Isaiah Trunk||Isaiah Trunk}} |pages=464–466, 472–474 |publisher=U of Nebraska Press |year=1972 |quote=The highest degree of cooperation was achieved when chairmen, or other leading {{tsl|en|Judenrat||Council}} members themselves, actively participated in preparing and executing acts of resistance, particularly in the course of liquidations of ghettos. [Prominent examples include [[華沙猶太區|Warsaw]],[[琴斯托霍瓦隔都|Częstochowa]], Radomsko, Pajęczno, Sasów, {{tsl|en|Pińsk Ghetto||Pińsk}}, Mołczadź, Iwaniska, {{tsl|en|Wilno Ghetto||Wilno}}, Nieśwież, Zdzięcioł (see: {{tsl|en|Zdzięcioł Ghetto||Zdzięcioł Ghetto}}), Tuczyn (Równe), and Marcinkańce ({{tsl|en|Grodno Ghetto||Grodno}}) among others] |isbn=978-0803294288 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D7bobfzrcCoC&q=Council+smuggling+arms |chapter=The Attitude of the Councils toward Physical Resistance |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103084453/http://books.google.com/books?id=D7bobfzrcCoC |archivedate=January 3, 2014 }} 另见： {{citation|title=The Holocaust: the Jewish tragedy |author={{tsl|en|Martin Gilbert||Martin Gilbert}} |publisher=Collins |year=1986 |page=828 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=hRJnAAAAMAAJ&q=brutalizing}}</ref>随着德国当局开始清理隔都，[[里加和约|波苏1939年边界]]两侧的100多个地点出现了武装抵抗，绝大多数发生在波兰东部。<ref name=ushmm2011>{{citation |title=Jewish Resistance |author=The Holocaust Encyclopedia |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |year=2011 |via=Internet Archive. |url=http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005213 |id=[https://web.archive.org/web/20120718225143/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/media_nm.php?ModuleId=10005213&MediaId=430 see map.] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126200522/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005213 |archivedate=January 26, 2012 }} 另见：{{citation |title=Armed Resistance |author=Shmuel Krakowski |publisher=YIVO |year=2010 |url=http://www.yivoencyclopedia.org/article.aspx/Armed_Resistance |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110602091431/http://www.yivoencyclopedia.org/article.aspx/Armed_Resistance |archivedate=June 2, 2011 }}</ref>5座主要城市、45座省级城镇、5个座要集中营和灭绝营、以及至少18个强迫劳动营中爆发了起义。<ref name="LermanCenter">{{citation |title=Resistance during the Holocaust |author=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |publisher=The Miles Lerman Center for the Study of Jewish Resistance |at=p. 6 of 56 in current document |url=https://www.ushmm.org/m/pdfs/20000831-resistance-bklt.pdf |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829054516/https://www.ushmm.org/m/pdfs/20000831-resistance-bklt.pdf |archivedate=August 29, 2017 }}.</ref><!--
值得注意的是，[[納粹集中營|納粹集中營]]中仅有犹太人发动过起义。<ref name="Bauer2000">{{citation |title=An Interview With Prof. Yehuda Bauer |author=Yad Vashem|publisher=Shoah Resource Center, The International School for Holocaust Studies |year=2000 |at=pp. 28–30 of 58 in current document|url=http://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%203856.pdf |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090320161945/http://www1.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%203856.pdf |archivedate=March 20, 2009 }}.</ref> <=意义不明 -->

早在1942年7月22日，犹太人就在波兰东部的[[涅斯維日|涅斯維日]]隔都发动了叛乱。9月3日，{{tsl|en|Łachwa Ghetto|拉科瓦隔都}}爆发起义；{{tsl|en|Mizocz Ghetto|米佐什隔都}}随后在10月14日爆发起义。1943年1月18日的[[華沙猶太區|华沙隔都]]{{tsl|en|Gross Aktion|华沙大行动|枪决行动}}导致[[華沙猶太區起義|二战中最大规模的犹太人起义]]在1943年4月19日爆发。6月25日，[[琴斯托霍瓦隔都|琴斯托霍瓦隔都]]爆发起义。1943年8月2日，[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡灭绝营]]的{{tsl|en|Sonderkommando|特别支队}}装备偷来的武器袭击了营地守卫。一天后，[[本津隔都|本津隔都]]和[[索斯诺维茨隔都|索斯诺维茨隔都]]爆发了起义。8月16日，{{tsl|en|Białystok Ghetto uprising|比亚韦斯托克隔都起义}}爆发。10月14日，[[索比布尔集中营|索比布尔集中营]]发生叛乱。1944年10月7日，起义者炸毁了奥斯威辛-比克瑙的一座焚尸炉。{{r|ushmm2011}}{{r|LermanCenter}}{{tsl|en|Łuck Ghetto|卢茨克隔都|卢茨克}}、{{tsl|en|Mińsk Mazowiecki Ghetto|马佐夫舍地区明斯克隔都|马佐夫舍地区明斯克}}、{{tsl|en|Pińsk Ghetto|平斯克隔都|平斯克}}、{{tsl|en|Poniatowa concentration camp|波尼亚托瓦隔都|波尼亚托瓦}}与[[维尔纽斯隔都|维尔纽斯]]也爆发了类似的抵抗运动。<ref>{{citation |title=Resistance in the Vilna Ghetto |author=The Holocaust Encyclopedia|url=https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005173 |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |year=2017 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803220421/https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005173 |archivedate=August 3, 2017 }}</ref>

== 波兰人与犹太人 ==
{{further|{{tsl|en|Polish Righteous among the Nations|波兰国际义人}}|犹太人大屠杀期间波兰人对犹太人的援助|{{tsl|en|Żegota|热戈塔委员会}}}}

只有10％的波兰犹太人在种族灭绝中幸存下来，这一比例是除了[[立陶宛猶太人大屠殺|立陶宛]]以外各纳粹占领国中最低的。然而，波兰民族的救援者占[[以色列猶太大屠殺紀念館|以色列猶太大屠殺紀念館]]认定的“[[國際義人|國際義人]]”中的大多数。根据{{tsl|en|Gunnar S. Paulsson|古纳尔·保罗森}}的说法，被认定的这些波兰人（超过6,000人）可能“只代表波兰救援者的冰山一角”。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}一些犹太人得到了[[德苏占领波兰|德占波兰]]的{{tsl|en|Polish resistance movement in World War II|第二次世界大战时期波兰的抵抗运动|抵抗运动}}组织{{tsl|en|Żegota|热戈塔委员会}}的有组织援助，这是波兰在德国占领的波兰抵抗的地下组织。<ref name="Shoa">[[以色列猶太大屠殺紀念館|Yad Vashem]] Shoa Resource Center,[http://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%206392.pdf Zegota] {{Wayback|url=http://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%206392.pdf |date=20131020062021 }}[https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.yadvashem.org%2Fodot_pdf%2FMicrosoft%2520Word%2520-%25206392.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 ] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020062021/http://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%206392.pdf |date=October 20, 2013 }}[https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20131020062021%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.yadvashem.org%2Fodot_pdf%2FMicrosoft%2520Word%2520-%25206392.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1] {{Wayback|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?url=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20131020062021%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.yadvashem.org%2Fodot_pdf%2FMicrosoft%2520Word%2520-%25206392.pdf&embedded=true&chrome=false&dov=1 |date=20190920094919 }}<span> October 20, 2013, at the</span>[[网站时光机|Wayback Machine]]<span>.</span>
, page 4/34 of the Report.</ref>

1941年11月10日，[[漢斯·法郎克|漢斯·法郎克]]将死刑范围扩大到“以任何方式”援助犹太人的波兰人，包括“带他们在家住一晚，或让他们搭任何类型的便车”，或者“喂养逃跑的犹太人，或卖给他们食物”。{{r|Paldiel}}该法律在所有主要城市以海报广而告之。德国人在东部前线上控制的其他地区也发布了类似的规定。<ref>[https://books.google.co.il/books?id=oVmSAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=poland+death+penalty+helping+jews&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVg8muh_3aAhVFiqQKHdZ9BHEQ6AEIIzAA#v=onepage&q=poland%20death%20penalty%20helping%20jews&f=falseHunt for the Jews] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511150037/https://books.google.co.il/books?id=oVmSAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=poland+death+penalty+helping+jews&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVg8muh_3aAhVFiqQKHdZ9BHEQ6AEIIzAA |date=May 11, 2018 }}, Jan Grabowski, page 55, Indiana University Press</ref><!--最严厉的惩罚是{{tsl|en|Józef and Wiktoria Ulma||株连全家}}的死刑。{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}-->超过700多名{{tsl|en|Polish Righteous among the Nations|波兰国际义人}}的称号是追授的，因为他们早已因帮助或庇护他们的犹太邻居而被德国人杀害。{{r|holocaustforgotten}}[[以色列猶太大屠殺紀念館|以色列猶太大屠殺紀念館]]认可的波兰义人中有许多来自首都。古纳尔·保罗森在对华沙犹太人的研究中证明，尽管条件更为严峻，但华沙的波兰公民援助和隐藏犹太人的比例与据信“更安全”的西欧德占城市相当。{{r|hnetradz}}

===反犹太主义===
波兰的反犹主义根深蒂固，有两个主要的动机：其一是声称犹太人污蔑了天主教信仰；其二是所谓的{{tsl|en|Żydokomuna|犹太共产主义}}学说。在20世纪30年代，波兰的天主教期刊可以和西欧的社会达尔文主义反犹主义和纳粹的传媒相当。然而，教会的教条禁止暴力行为，而直到20世纪30年代中期暴力行为才变得更加普遍。与德国的反犹太主义不同，波兰的反犹太主义者反对对犹太人实施种族灭绝或反犹骚乱的主张，而是主张大规模的移民。<ref>''This last statement is based on the fact that Polish Antisemitism, even during the war, was not murderous in nature and did not speak in terms of outright liquidation except on its outermost fringes. It expressed extreme messages and unequivocal conclusions–the imperative of mass Jewish emigration from Poland–but did not advocate pogroms or genocide''Were These Ordinary Poles?
Daniel Blatman {{cite web |url=https://www.yadvashem.org/articles/academic/were-these-ordinary-poles.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2018-05-19 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180520055802/https://www.yadvashem.org/articles/academic/were-these-ordinary-poles.html |archivedate=May 20, 2018 }}</ref>德国和苏联的占领带来了波兰反犹主义的突然高潮。波兰人的看法基于认定共产党人有着“犹太合作”，以及波兰民族自身对犹太人的仇恨。勒索犹太人以及向德国当局告发犹太人的“{{tsl|en|szmalcownik|猪油仔}}”也是普通的波兰人，但他们的行为不在全波兰民族的共识范围之内。巴巴罗萨行动之后，波兰人在1941年的[[耶德瓦布内反犹骚乱|耶德瓦布内反犹骚乱]]中袭击并杀害了犹太人，波兰东部的其他地方也发生了类似事件。1944年至1946年间也有波兰人殴打和杀害犹太人的事件，其中包括[[凯尔采反犹骚乱|凯尔采反犹骚乱]]；这一时期类似事件的主要诱因是波兰人接管的犹太财产的处置问题。<ref>[https://books.google.co.il/books?id=-_Si5OP6cjkC&pg=PR12&lpg=PR12&dq=Polish+Anti+Semitism:+A+National+Psychosis?+blatman&source=bl&ots=XaZn_1EDUz&sig=eDd515UwdAeuOXJIq04nBlJXAvU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjdubTJpYXbAhXE2qQKHXlqCl0Q6AEwAHoECAAQLg#v=onepage&q=national%20psychosis&f=falseJews and the Sporting Life: Studies in Contemporary Jewry XXIII (Polish Antisemitism: A National Pshychosis?)]{{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515045215/https://books.google.co.il/books?id=-_Si5OP6cjkC&pg=PR12&lpg=PR12&dq=Polish+Anti+Semitism%3A+A+National+Psychosis%3F+blatman&source=bl&ots=XaZn_1EDUz&sig=eDd515UwdAeuOXJIq04nBlJXAvU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjdubTJpYXbAhXE2qQKHXlqCl0Q6AEwAHoECAAQLg|date=May 15, 2018 }}, Daniel Blatman in volume edited by  Ezra Mendelsohn, Oxford University Press, pages 213–225</ref>

===救援与援助===
{{further|{{tsl|en|World War II casualties of Poland|第二次世界大战时期波兰的伤亡}}|犹太人大屠杀期间波兰人对犹太人的援助}}
