根据现代标准，绝大多数波兰犹太人都属于“显著的少数民族”，可以通过语言、行为和外表来区分。{{r|StopnHe65}}在1931年的波兰全国人口普查中，只有12％的犹太人宣称波兰语是他们的第一语言，而79％的人将[[意第緒語|意第緒語]]列为他们的母语，另有9％的[[希伯来语|希伯来语]]母语者。<ref name="GUS1931">{{cite book |title=Drugi Powszechny Spis Ludności, 9.XII.1931 |work={{tsl|en|Polish census of 1931||Polish census of 1931}}. Table 10, page 30 in current document|url=http://statlibr.stat.gov.pl/exlibris/aleph/a22_1/apache_media/VUNVGMLANSCQQFGYHCN3VDLK12A9U5.pdf |author=Główny Urząd Statystyczny |location=Warsaw |year=1938|id=PDF file, direct download |language=pl |quote=Religion and Native Language (total). Section, Jewish: 3,113,933 with Yiddish: 2,489,034 and Hebrew: 243,539|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402143415/http://statlibr.stat.gov.pl/exlibris/aleph/a22_1/apache_media/VUNVGMLANSCQQFGYHCN3VDLK12A9U5.pdf|archivedate=April 2, 2015 }}.</ref>在包括波兰省会城市在内的许多城市与{{tsl|en|shtetl|犹太人小镇|乡镇}}的劳动力市场中，存在数量庞大且文化不适应的少数群体，{{r|StopnHe65}}，导致了竞争压力。<ref>{{citation |title=God's Playground |at=(Polish edition), Second volume, pp. 512–513 |author={{tsl|en|Norman Davies||Norman Davies}} |year=1979}}; {{citation |title=Economic Change and the National Question in Twentieth-century Europe |authors={{tsl|en|Alice Teichova||Alice Teichova}}, Herbert Matis, Jaroslav Pátek |year=2000 |pages=342–344 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8UVxY-8Xk-sC&q=minorities+Nowogrodek |isbn=9781139427654 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924172728/https://books.google.com/books?id=8UVxY-8Xk-sC&q=minorities+Nowogrodek |dead-url=no }}; {{citation |title=Business environment in 1926–1929 |work=Jewish history of Radom |authors=Gedeon & Marta Kubiszyn |publisher=[[Virtual_Shtetl|Virtual Shtetl]] |language=pl |at=page 2 of 6 |url=http://www.sztetl.org.pl/pl/article/radom/5,historia/?action=view&page=1 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811055134/http://www.sztetl.org.pl/pl/article/radom/5,historia/?action=view&page=1 |archivedate=2017-08-11 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}; {{citation |title=Lubartow during the Holocaust in occupied Poland |url=http://www.jhi.pl/en/gminy/miasto/423.html |publisher=Taube Foundation for Jewish Life and Culture |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120216021119/http://www.jhi.pl/en/gminy/miasto/423.html |archivedate=February 16, 2012 }}.</ref>然而古纳尔·保罗森总结道，不能因此而直接得到战时波兰人-犹太人关系的相关结论：当犹太人大屠杀开始后，“如果不考虑战争行为和纳粹的背信弃义，一个躲藏在华沙的犹太人活下来的机会绝不会比藏在荷兰更差。”{{r|GSPau-JHE}}

在犹太人区隔都清场期临近结束时，大量犹太人设法逃到“雅利安”一方，{{r|GSPau-JHE}}并在波兰救助者的帮助下生存。纳粹占领期间，大多数波兰人都在为自身的生存而绝望地斗争。他们无法阻止德国人消灭犹太人。1939年至1945年间，有近280万{{tsl|en|gentile|非犹太人|非犹太}}波兰人死于纳粹手中，15万人因苏联镇压而死亡；<ref name="Materski&Szarota">{{harvp|Materski|Szarota|2009|loc=page 9.}}</ref>死亡总数占波兰战前人口的五分之一。<ref name="Piotrowski305">{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|pp=305–|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=hC0-dk7vpM8C&lpg=PA305&vq=Poland's%20Losses%20Caused%20Description&pg=PA305  'Poland's losses.']}}</ref>他们的死因是{{tsl|en|World War II casualties of Poland|第二次世界大战时期波兰的伤亡|故意的战争行为}}的结果，<ref>{{harvp|Materski|Szarota|2009|loc=page 16.}}</ref>包括大规模屠杀、集中营监禁、强迫劳动、营养不良、疾病、绑架和驱逐。<ref>{{harvp|Materski|Szarota|2009|loc=page 28. Some 800,000 Poles perished in concentration camps and mass murders.}}</ref>然而，有许多波兰人冒着死亡的风险隐藏整个犹太家庭，或以慈悲为由帮助犹太人。{{r|Żarski}}如果犹太人被德国人发现，救助他们的波兰人有时会被这些犹太人告发，招致总督府内一整个援助网的灭顶之灾。<ref name="WZaj:152–201"/>沙尔斯基-扎伊德勒（Żarski-Zajdler）引用数据称，与非犹太波兰人一同藏匿的犹太人人数约为45万。<ref name="Żarski">{{cite book |last=Żarski-Zajdler |first=Władysław |year=1968 |title=Martyrologia ludności żydowskiej i pomoc społeczeństwa polskiego |trans-title=Martyrdom of the Jewish people and their rescue by the Polish society |location=Warsaw |publisher=ZBoWiD |page=16 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_2S-ZAkAy7EC&q=Zajdler+Martyrologia |id=[in:] Lucas (2013), p.14. Note 21 to "Introduction." |isbn=978-0813143323 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902013255/https://books.google.com/books?id=_2S-ZAkAy7EC&q=Zajdler+Martyrologia |dead-url=no }}</ref>可能有100万名非犹太波兰人帮助过他们的犹太邻居。{{r|HG}}历史学家{{tsl|en|Richard C. Lukas|理查德·卢卡斯}}{{r|Lukas1989}}估计波兰援助者的数量高达300万；这一数目与其他作者所引用的估计相似。<ref name="Goldberg2012">{{cite book |title=Needle in the Bone: How a Holocaust Survivor and a Polish Resistance Fighter Beat the Odds and Found Each Other |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=p2yWClrSYL0C&pg=PA6 |author=Caryn Mirriam-Goldberg |year=2012 |quote=Approximately 3 million Poles rescued, hid, or otherwise helped Jews during the war, and fewer than a thousand denounced Jews to the Nazis. |isbn=978-1612345680 |page=6 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819171903/https://books.google.com/books?id=p2yWClrSYL0C&pg=PA6 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Kwiatkowski2016">{{cite book |title=The Country That Refused to Die: The Story of the People of Poland |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L57TDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT347 |author=Richard Kwiatkowski |year=2016 |isbn=978-1524509156 |quote=The number of Poles estimated to be actively involved in the rescue of Jews is estimated between one and three million. |page=347 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819141008/https://books.google.com/books?id=L57TDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT347 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Marshall2000">{{cite book |title=Moral geographies: ethics in a world of difference |page=112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9SwSAQAAIAAJ&q=Poles+involved |author=David Marshall Smith |year=2000 |quote=It has been estimated that a million or more Poles were involved in helping Jews. |isbn=9780748612789 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925094740/https://books.google.com/books?id=9SwSAQAAIAAJ&q=Poles+involved |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Lukas2013">{{harvp|Lukas|1989|page=13}} – Recent research suggests that a million Poles were involved, but some estimates go as high as three million.[https://books.google.com/books?id=_2S-ZAkAy7EC&pg=PA13 Lukas, 2013 edition.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705225949/https://books.google.com/books?id=_2S-ZAkAy7EC&pg=PA13 |date=July 5, 2018 }} {{ISBN|0813143322}}.</ref>

