整个{{tsl|en|History of Poland (1939–1945)|波兰历史(1939-1945)|第二次世界大战期间}}，波兰从未组建任何[[通敌|纳粹勾结者政府]]。{{r|JC}}正如{{tsl|en|Tadeusz Piotrowski|塔德乌什·彼得罗夫斯基|彼得罗夫斯基}}指出，“[[波蘭人|波蘭人]]中从来没有出现过{{tsl|en|Quisling|吉斯林分子}}或任何特别的波兰党卫队师。相比之下，几乎所有其他欧洲国家都为纳粹德国提供了这两种勾结者。”<ref>{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|p=84|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=NBbnrEMswbUC&q=produced+Quisling+contrast 'Quisling.']}}</ref>[[波蘭地下國|波蘭地下國]]强烈反对在反犹迫害中的合作，并代表[[波蘭家鄉軍|波兰救国军]]军事法庭威胁称所有针对他们的线人将会被处死。<ref>{{cite book |title=Polacy ratujący Żydów w latach II wojny światowej |trans-title=Poles rescuing Jews during World War II|publisher=[[国家记忆研究院|Institute of National Remembrance]] |work=Zeszyty IPN, Wybór Tekstów |date=2008 |location=Warsaw |editor1=Piotr Chojnacki |editor2=Dorota Mazek |pp=7, 18, 23, 31 |quote=Kierownictwo Walki Cywilnej w "Biuletynie Informacyjnym" ostrzega "szmalcowników" i denuncjatorów przed konsekwencjami grożącymi im ze strony władz państwa podziemnego.<sup> [p.37 in PDF]</sup> Ot, widzi pan, sprawa jednej litery sprawia ogromną różnicę. Ratować i uratować! Ratowaliśmy kilkadziesiąt razy więcej ludzi, niż uratowaliśmy. – {{tsl|en|Władysław Bartoszewski||Władysław Bartoszewski}}<sup> [p.7]</sup>}}</ref>然而，{{tsl|en|History of Poland (1939–1945)|波兰历史(1939-1945)|持续的战争暴行}}导致波兰传统社会规范和价值观崩溃。{{r|MP159}}<ref name="Piotrowski-66">{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=hC0-dk7vpM8C&q=%22Jews+collaborating%22 p. 66. 'Collaborating.']}}</ref>有些人背叛了躲藏起来的犹太人，连同保护他们的波兰人。{{r|Grab}}根据波兰{{tsl|en|Special Courts|特别法庭}}的叛国罪死刑判决数量，敲诈勒索犹太人的人数约有数千人。.<ref name="Lukas">{{cite book |first=Richard C. |last=Lukas |url=https://books.google.com/?id=lz9obsxmuW4C&pg=PA13#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Out of the Inferno: Poles Remember the Holocaust |publisher=University Press of Kentucky |year=1989 |page=13 |isbn=978-0813116921}} ''Also in:'' {{cite book |first=Richard C. |last=Lukas|title=The Forgotten Holocaust: The Poles Under German Occupation, 1939–1944 |publisher=University Press of Kentucky |year=1986 |isbn=978-0781809016|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Lv1mAAAAMAAJ&q=Special+Courts |page=120}}</ref>古纳尔·保罗森在他的评论中表示，他可能会认定2万名波兰人拥有“丑陋的企图”。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://isurvived.org/4Debates/paulsson_supplement.html |title=Dr. Paulsson's Commentary in Refuting the Editor's "Hate Poles" Campaign |website=isurvived.org|access-date=2018-06-07 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141040/http://isurvived.org/4Debates/paulsson_supplement.html |archivedate=June 12, 2018 }}</ref>大屠杀的证词证实，当犹太人被困在隔都时，一些犹太人利用了其他犹太人社会经济地位的内幕信息获利（参见[[13号小组|13号小组]]）。<ref name="MP159">{{cite journal |last1=Paul |first1=Mark |title=Patterns of Cooperation, Collaboration and Betrayal: Jews, Germans and Poles in Occupied Poland during World War II |date=September 2015 |journal=Glaukopis |series=Foreign language studies |at=159/344 in PDF |url=http://www.glaukopis.pl/images/artykuly-obcojezyczne/Collaboration.pdf |accessdate=25 February 2016 |quote=The Jewish looters knew better than anyone else "where to dig for valuables." Testimonies of Anzel Daches, Majer Gdański, Laja Goldman, Mojżesz Klajman, Chana Kohn, Jakub Libman, and Izrael Szerman, dated October 13, 1947; the {{tsl|en|Jewish Historical Institute||Jewish Historical Institute}} Archive, record group 301, number 2932. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303071056/http://www.glaukopis.pl/images/artykuly-obcojezyczne/Collaboration.pdf |archivedate=2016-03-03 |author= }}</ref>

{{tsl|en|John Connelly (historian)|约翰·康奈利(历史学家)|约翰·康奈利}}和{{tsl|en|Leszek Gondek|莱谢克·贡德克}}认为，在欧洲和世界历史的背景下，波兰的通敌现象是边缘化的。{{r|JC}}首次违反道德界限的行为发生在 [[蘇聯入侵波蘭|苏联占领时期]]：1940年-1941年期间，苏联将波兰人家庭大规模向东{{tsl|en|Soviet repressions of Polish citizens (1939–1946)|苏联对波兰公民的打压(1939-1946)|发配至西伯利亚}}，[[内务人民委员部|内务人民委员部]]武装的犹太民兵（opaskowcy）参与了相关行动。{{r|HDoP}}{{r|B-C-S}}{{r|TSts}}{{r|pacwashmetrodiv}}1941年7月10日，在[[巴巴羅薩行動|巴巴羅薩行動]]开始时，300多名[[耶德瓦布内|耶德瓦布内]]的犹太人被一群波兰人[[耶德瓦布内反犹骚乱|活活烧死在一座谷仓里]]；根据[[国家记忆研究院|国家记忆研究院]]最终调查结果，德国的[[秩序警察|秩序警察]]当时也在现场。{{r|Jedwabne Tragedy: Final Findings}}关于耶德瓦布内事件的经过仍然存在争议；争论的因素包括部署在{{tsl|en|Bezirk Bialystok|比亚里斯托克区}}的{{tsl|en|Einsatzkommando|别动支队|齐辛瑙-施罗特斯堡别动队}}（由[[親衛隊上級突擊隊領袖|党卫队二级突击队中队长]]{{tsl|en|Hermann Schaper|赫尔曼·沙佩尔}}领导）的作用、<ref name="Rossino">{{cite journal |first=Alexander B. |last=Rossino |url=http://myinternetarchive-recovery.blogspot.ca/2011/04/polish-neighbors-and-german-invaders.html |title=Polish 'Neighbors' and German Invaders: Contextualizing Anti-Jewish Violence in the Białystok District during the Opening Weeks of Operation Barbarossa |journal=Polin: Studies in Polish Jewry |volume=16 |date=2003 |id=''References:'' №58. ''The Partisan: From the Valley of Death to Mount Zion'' by Yitzhak Arad; №59. ''The Lesser of Two Evils: Eastern European Jewry under Soviet Rule, 1939–1941'' by Dov Levin; and №97. Abschlussbericht, 17 March 1964 in ZStL, 5 AR-Z 13/62, p. 164 |via=Internet Archive  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222014730/http://myinternetarchive-recovery.blogspot.ca/2011/04/polish-neighbors-and-german-invaders.html |archivedate=February 22, 2014 }}</ref><ref name="Wrobel">{{cite book |title=Polish-Jewish Relations |first=Piotr |last=Wróbel |publisher={{tsl|en|Northwestern University Press||Northwestern University Press}} |year=2006 |pages=391–396 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=--fhfkLjI8AC&pg=PA392&dq=%22It+is+unfortunate%22+%22that+Jan+Gross+neglected+the+German+part+of+his+research%22 |work={{tsl|en|Dagmar Herzog||Dagmar Herzog}}: Lessons and Legacies: The Holocaust in international perspective |isbn=978-0-8101-2370-0 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2019-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005054137/https://books.google.com/books?id=--fhfkLjI8AC&pg=PA392&dq=%22It+is+unfortunate%22+%22that+Jan+Gross+neglected+the+German+part+of+his+research%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>德国纳粹的压力，以及广泛存在的对犹太人1939年热烈欢迎红军的憎恨。{{r|HDoP}}<ref name="B-C-S">{{cite book |title=Shared History, Divided Memory: Jews and Others in Soviet-occupied Poland, 1939–1941 |first1=Elazar |last1=Barkan |first2=Elizabeth A. |last2=Cole |first3=Kai |last3=Struve |isbn=978-3865832405 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_BbvQbiaqAEC&q=warmly+welcomed+aggression |pages=136, 151 |year=2007 |publisher=Leipziger Universitätsverlag |quote=In dozens of towns and settlements, attacks were carried out by "militias", "self-defence groups" and ''opaskowcy'' (called such for the red armbands they wore), which were made up primarily of Jews and Belarussians.<sup>[p.151]</sup> |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2019-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822201030/https://books.google.com/books?id=_BbvQbiaqAEC&q=warmly+welcomed+aggression |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{r|TSts}}{{r|pacwashmetrodiv}}

根据政治家{{tsl|en|Stefan Korboński|斯特凡·科尔本斯基}}的说法，{{tsl|en|National Armed Forces|国家武装部队(波兰)|国家武装部队}}（NSZ）的一些成员参与了对亲苏联地下组织的犹太人成员的处决。{{r|Piotrowski1998_95}}历史学家{{tsl|en|Richard C. Lukas|理查德·卢卡斯}}和{{tsl|en|Tadeusz Piotrowski|塔德乌什·彼得罗夫斯基}}写道，NSZ向犹太人提供援助，并将他们与{{tsl|en|Polish Righteous Among the Nations|波兰国际义人}}一起列入他们的队伍。{{r|Piotrowski1998_96}}NSZ圣十字旅救出了[[霍利紹夫|霍利紹夫]]集中营的约1,000名囚犯中的280名犹太妇女。NSZ的一名犹太游击队员菲力克斯·帕利（Feliks Parry）表示，他们中的大多数人“对他们组织的意识形态基础没有丝毫概念”而且并不关心，只关注抵抗纳粹分子。{{r|Piotrowski1998_977142}}在战后的波兰，{{tsl|en|Ministry of Public Security of Poland|波兰公安部|共产党秘密警察}}经常折磨NSZ叛乱分子，迫使他们承认杀害了犹太人，以及犯下了其他所谓的罪行；其中最值得注意的是1946年在卢布林对23名NSZ军官的审判。即使审讯结束，{{tsl|en|Ministry of Public Security of Poland|波兰公安部|公安部}}对[[政治犯|政治犯]]的折磨并不会停止。如果NSZ被告在法庭上翻供否认“杀害犹太人”，也会遭受肉体折磨。{{r|polak}}

==波兰民族是否属于犹太人大屠杀的受害者==

纳粹对东欧的[[東方總計畫|长期计划]]包括波兰的[[种族清洗|种族清洗]]，据纳粹估计该计划会导致约85％的波兰人死亡。<ref name="WFF">{{cite web |title=Generalplan Ost (General Plan East). The Nazi evolution in German foreign policy. Documentary sources |author=Various authors |publisher=World Future Fund |work=Versions of the GPO |year=2003 |location=Alexandria, VA |url=http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/GPO/gpo%20sources.htm#Versions%20of%20the%20GPO |id=Resources: Janusz Gumkowski and Kazimierz Leszczynski,''Hitler's Plans for Eastern Europe. Ibid.'' |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070102104440/http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/GPO/gpo%20sources.htm#Versions%20of%20the%20GPO |archivedate=2007-01-02 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}</ref>截至战争结束时，该计划大部分没有实现。

根据Donald Niewyk和Francis Nicosia的说法，“波兰人和其他斯拉夫人团体是否属于犹太人大屠杀受害者”这一问题，取决于是应根据纳粹的动机界定大屠杀，还是应根据纳粹实现其种族议程的程度来界定大屠杀。采取第一种立场的人认为，纳粹在波兰、乌克兰、白俄罗斯和苏联的暴行是“纳粹蔑视'非人'的直接结果”；{{r|ColumbiaGuide|pp=49}}采取第二种立场的人指出，这些人的死亡“比犹太人、吉普赛人和残疾人（的灭绝）更具选择性”，并且很难区分“出于种族动机杀害的波兰人和苏联公民，[以及]德国军事行动直接或间接杀害的两国公民。”{{r|ColumbiaGuide|pp=49}}Niewyk和Niocosia自身认同第二种立场。{{r|ColumbiaGuide|pp=52}}

==波兰少数民族在犹太人大屠杀中的角色==
{{Jewish Polish history}}
{{Main|德意志裔人|党卫队国外德意志民族事务部|{{tsl|en|Volksdeutscher Selbstschutz|德意志裔自卫队}}|{{tsl|en|Sonderdienst|特勤队(纳粹德国)|特勤队}}}}

二战爆发前的波兰共和国是一个多元文化的国家，其人口的近三分之一来自少数民族：13.9％的乌克兰人; 10％的犹太人; 3.1％白俄罗斯人; 2.3％的德裔；以及3.4％的捷克人、立陶宛人和俄罗斯人。{{r|ePWN}}波兰1918年重获独立之后不久，来自苏维埃共和国的大约50万难民在最初的自发逃亡中来到波兰。难民中以来自乌克兰的居多（参见[[栅栏区|栅栏区]]）——内战期间乌克兰发生了多达2,000起反犹骚乱。<ref>{{cite book |author=Sharman Kadish |title=Bolsheviks and British Jews: The Anglo-Jewish Community, Britain, and the Russian Revolution |publisher=Routledge |page=80 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rhkA1VpX5KQC&q=Civil+War+pogroms |isbn=978-0-7146-3371-8 |year=1992 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819205806/https://books.google.com/books?id=rhkA1VpX5KQC&q=Civil+War+pogroms |dead-url=no }}</ref>在1919年11月到1924年6月的第二次移民浪潮中，约有120万人离开苏联领土前往新生的波兰。据估计约有46万名难民将波兰语作为第一语言。<ref name="ePWN">{{cite encyclopedia|encyclopedia=Encyklopedia PWN |title=Rosja. Polonia i Polacy |first=Stanisław |last=Gregorowicz |url=http://encyklopedia.pwn.pl/haslo/Rosja-Polonia-i-Polacy;4575227.html |publisher={{tsl|en|Polish Scientific Publishers PWN||Polish Scientific Publishers PWN}} |series=Online |year=2016 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406045946/http://encyklopedia.pwn.pl/haslo/Rosja-Polonia-i-Polacy;4575227.html |archivedate=April 6, 2016 }}</ref><ref name=JM>{{cite book |first=Joseph |last=Marcus |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=82ncGA4GuN4C&q=national+minorities |title=Social and political history of the Jews in Poland, 1919–1939 |pages=17–19 |publisher=Walter de Gruyter |year=1983 |isbn=978-90-279-3239-6 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171022215605/https://books.google.com/books?id=82ncGA4GuN4C |archivedate=October 22, 2017 }}</ref>1933年至1938年间，约有2.5万名[[德国犹太人|德国犹太人]]逃离[[納粹德國|納粹德國]]前往波兰寻求庇护。<ref name="Gilbert-1">{{cite book |title=The Routledge Atlas of the Holocaust |first=Martin |last=Gilbert |publisher=Psychology Press |year=2002 |at=p. 23, Map 15: Jewish Refugees Find Haven in Europe, 1933–1938 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PnE6TXjt4hkC&q=HAVENS+1933-1938 |isbn=978-0-415-28146-1 |via=Google Books |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819174939/https://books.google.com/books?id=PnE6TXjt4hkC&q=HAVENS+1933-1938 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

约有一百万波兰公民属于德裔少数民族。<ref>{{cite book |title=Historical Dictionary of Poland 1945-1996 |first=Piotr |last=Wróbel |publisher=Routledge |year=2014 |page=108 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Xcm2AgAAQBAJ&q=Before+1939+colonization |isbn=978-1135926946 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820020305/https://books.google.com/books?id=Xcm2AgAAQBAJ&q=Before+1939+colonization |dead-url=no }}</ref>1939年德苏入侵之后，又有118万名说德语的人来到波兰，其中有些{{tsl|en|Reichsdeutsche|帝国德意志人|来自帝国}}，也有些来自东部的{{tsl|en|Heim ins Reich|回归帝国|几乎一无所有}}的[[德意志裔人|德意志裔人]]。<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d-rrAAAAMAAJ&q=1,180,+000+persons |title=Demographic developments in Eastern Europe |publisher=Praeger |year=1977 |p=314 |first=Leszek A. |last=Kosiński |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819034938/https://books.google.com/books?id=d-rrAAAAMAAJ&q=1,180,+000+persons |dead-url=no }}</ref>数百名德裔波兰人加入了纳粹的{{tsl|en|Volksdeutscher Selbstschutz|德意志裔自卫队}}，以及1940年5月[[大區長官|大區長官]][[漢斯·法郎克|漢斯·法郎克]]在克拉科夫成立的{{tsl|en|Sonderdienst|特勤队(纳粹德国)|特勤队}}部队。<ref name="Roszkowski">{{cite web |first=Wojciech |last=Roszkowski |url=http://tygodnik.onet.pl/1,16768,druk.html |title=History: The Zero Hour |trans-title=Historia: Godzina zero |publisher=Tygodnik.Onet.pl weekly |date=4 November 2008 |accessdate=18 May 2014 |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512015340/http://tygodnik.onet.pl/1,16768,druk.html |archivedate=May 12, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Yad Vashem">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JcDXaeukt4sC&q=1942+%22Minsk+Mazowiecki%22 |title=Yad Vashem Studies |publisher=Wallstein Verlag |year=2001 |author=The Erwin and Riva Baker Memorial Collection |pages=57– |issn=0084-3296 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819130359/https://books.google.com/books?id=JcDXaeukt4sC&q=1942+%22Minsk+Mazowiecki%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在逃往{{tsl|en|General Government administration|波兰总督府行政机关|波兰总督府辖区}}的大约3万名乌克兰民族主义者中，有数千人加入了{{tsl|pl|Grupy marszowe OUN|乌克兰民族主义组织冲锋队}}，在{{tsl|en|Kraków District|克拉科夫区}}的各个德国基地接受培训，担任破坏者、口译员和民兵。<ref name="Getter">{{cite journal |publisher=Kantor Program Papers |others=Roni Stauber, Beryl Belsky |date=June 2012 |title=Honoring the Collaborators – The Ukrainian Case |first=Irena |last=Cantorovich |url=http://kantorcenter.tau.ac.il/sites/default/files/ukraine-collaborators_3.pdf |quote=When the Soviets occupied eastern Galicia, some 30,000 Ukrainian nationalists fled to the General Government. In 1940 the Germans began to set up military training units of Ukrainians, and in the spring of 1941 Ukrainian units were established by the Wehrmacht. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170510065038/http://kantorcenter.tau.ac.il/sites/default/files/ukraine-collaborators_3.pdf |archivedate=2017-05-10 |journal= |author= |access-date=2019-03-19 }} ''See also:'' {{cite web |url=http://www.scribd.com/doc/150069634/Marek-Getter-1996-Policja-Polska-w-Generalnym-Gubernatorstwie-1939-1945-Przegl%C4%85d-Policyjny-nr-1-2-Wydawnictwo-Wy%C5%BCszej-Szko%C5%82y-Policji-w-Szczytni |title=Policja w Generalnym Gubernatorstwie 1939–1945 |publisher=Przegląd Policyjny nr 1-2. Wydawnictwo Wyższej Szkoły Policji w Szczytnie |year=1996 |author=Marek Getter |pages=1–22 |id=WebCite cache |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Hen2CZJW?url=http://www.scribd.com/doc/150069634/Marek-Getter-1996-Policja-Polska-w-Generalnym-Gubernatorstwie-1939-1945-Przegl%C4%85d-Policyjny-nr-1-2-Wydawnictwo-Wy%C5%BCszej-Szko%C5%82y-Policji-w-Szczytni |archivedate=June 26, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=U.S. Intelligence and the Nazis |first=Richard |last=Breitman |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2005 |isbn=978-0521617949 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GnkBYN8ipYcC&q=recruit+Ukrainians+1940 |page=249 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017062731/https://books.google.com/books?id=GnkBYN8ipYcC&q=recruit+Ukrainians+1940 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在具有相当数量的德裔和亲德少数民族的城市，特勤队的存在对试图帮助隔都犹太人的非犹太波兰人构成了严重威胁：{{tsl|en|Izbica Ghetto|伊兹比察隔都|伊兹比察}}、{{tsl|en|Łuck Ghetto|卢茨克隔都|卢茨克}}和{{tsl|en|Mińsk Mazowiecki Ghetto|马佐夫舍地区明斯克隔都|马佐夫舍地区明斯克}}等地的隔都就属于这种情况。[[蘇聯入侵波蘭|苏联入侵]][[波兰前东部领土|波兰前东部领土]]之后，俄罗斯人占领的东部省份产生了特别明显的反犹太主义态度。波兰当地人民目睹了苏联镇压自己同胞，并{{tsl|en|Sybirak|波兰西伯利亚流放者|大规模流放至西伯利亚}}{{r|Szarota2009}}{{r|HDoP}}。[[内务人民委员部|苏联安全机构]]执行了迫害波兰人的行动；此外，一些当地犹太人组成民兵，接管关键行政职务，<ref>{{harvp|Lukas|2001|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=Lv1mAAAAMAAJ&q=%22helped+to+disarm+Polish+soldiers%22  ''The forgotten Holocaust'', page 128.]}}</ref>并与内务人民委员部合作。其他人则认为，在复仇的推动下，[[犹太布尔什维主义|犹太共产党人]]在背叛波兰族和其他非犹太人的受害者方面表现突出。{{r|pacwashmetrodiv}}{{r|archive}}

===受德国启发的屠杀事件===
{{further|博纳利大屠杀|1941年利沃夫反犹骚乱|斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫隔都|l3=斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫隔都大屠杀}}

波兰东部占领区发生了多起受德国人启发的大屠杀事件，本地人民的积极参与其中。这种大屠杀的指导方针是[[萊因哈德·海德里希|萊因哈德·海德里希]]制定的：{{r|B-M}}他命令他的军官在德国军队新占领的领土上挑拨反犹太骚乱。{{r|Steinl30}}{{r|P-M}}在战前波兰第五大城市，[[維爾諾省|維爾諾省]]首府[[维尔纽斯|维尔诺]]（今维尔纽斯）的[[维尔纽斯隔都|隔都]]建立前，<ref name="JTG">{{cite book |title=Revolution from Abroad: The Soviet Conquest of Poland's Western Ukraine and Western Belorussia |publisher=Princeton University Press |author=Gross, Jan Tomasz |year=2002 |page=3 |isbn=978-0-691-09603-2}}</ref>{{tsl|en|Einsatzkommando|别动支队|德国支队}}和{{tsl|en|Lithuanian Auxiliary Police Battalions|立陶宛辅助警察营}}在1941年末的[[博纳利大屠杀|博纳利大屠杀]]期间杀死了21,000多名犹太人。<ref name="Snyder">{{cite book |first=Timothy |last=Snyder |title=The Reconstruction of Nations: Poland, Ukraine, Lithuania, Belarus, 1569–1999 |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=978-0-300-10586-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xSpEynLxJ1MC&q=%28Ypatingas+Burys%29 |via=Google Books, preview |pages=84–89|year=2003}}</ref>当时，维尔诺只有一小部分讲[[立陶宛语|立陶宛语]]的少数民族，约占该市人口的6％.<ref name="muller">{{cite book |title=Memory and Power in Post-War Europe: Studies in the Presence of the Past |publisher=Cambridge University Press |author=Müller, Jan-Werner |year=2002 |page=47|isbn=978-0-521-00070-3}}</ref>在乌克兰武装分子在东部城市[[利沃夫隔都|利沃夫]]犯下的一系列[[1941年利沃夫反犹骚乱|反犹骚乱]]中，大约6,000名波兰犹太人在1941年6月30日至7月29日期间在街头遇害，其中有3,000人被C别动队逮捕并枪决。<ref name="Longerich194">{{cite book |last=Longerich |first=Peter |title=Holocaust: The Nazi Persecution and Murder of the Jews |year=2010|publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford; New York |isbn=978-0-19-280436-5 |pages=194– |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cxYqYIn73SgC&lpg=PA194&vq=Petljura%20Days&pg=PA194 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170201235512/https://books.google.com/books?id=cxYqYIn73SgC|archivedate=February 1, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia – Lwów |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum|url=http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005171 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307103305/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10005171 |archivedate=March 7, 2012 }}</ref>由[[乌克兰民族主义者组织|乌克兰民族主义者组织]]（OUN）组建的{{tsl|en|Ukrainian People's Militia|乌克兰人民民兵|乌克兰民兵组织}}在[[党卫队|党卫队]]的赞许下，在波兰东南部的数十个地点散播恐怖。<ref name="Grelka2005">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H6cdeIGI8uwC&lpg=PA284&vq=%22ukrainische%20Miliz%22&pg=PA283 |title=Ukrainischen Miliz |publisher=Otto Harrassowitz Verlag |work=Die ukrainische Nationalbewegung unter deutscher Besatzungsherrschaft 1918 und 1941/42 |year=2005 |author=Dr. Frank Grelka |pages=283–284 |quote=RSHA von einer begrüßenswerten Aktivitat der ukrainischen Bevolkerung in den ersten Stunden nach dem Abzug der Sowjettruppen. |isbn=978-3-447-05259-7 |location=[[奥得河畔法兰克福欧洲大学|Viadrina European University]] |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017115419/https://books.google.com/books?id=H6cdeIGI8uwC&lpg=PA284&vq=%22ukrainische%20Miliz%22&pg=PA283 |dead-url=no }} ''For the German administrative divisions of Polish kresy with prominent Jewish communities destroyed under Nazi occupation, see:'' {{citation |title=The Death of the Shtetl |first=Yehuda |last=Bauer |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ACMyoc07PaQC&q=kresy+Brest+Lutsk+Rowne |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2009 |isbn=978-0300152098 |pages=1–6, 65 |accessdate=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926005643/https://books.google.com/books?id=ACMyoc07PaQC&q=kresy+Brest+Lutsk+Rowne |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

[[File:Lviv_pogrom_(June_-_July_1941).jpg|thumb]]期间，在梅多瓦街上（Medova）被暴徒追赶的犹太妇女。]]

早在[[塔爾諾波爾省|塔爾諾波爾省]][[捷尔诺波尔|省会]]的[[塔尔诺波尔隔都|隔都]]成立之前，国防军抵达该市两天后，塔尔诺波尔就有多达2,000名犹太人被杀，<ref>{{cite web |first1=Robert |last1=Kuwałek |first2=Eugeniusz |last2=Riadczenko |first3=Adam |last3=Marczewski |year=2015 |title=Tarnopol |others=Translated by Katarzyna Czoków and Magdalena Wójcik |website=[[Virtual_Shtetl|Virtual Shtetl]] |pp=3–4 |url=http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/tarnopol/5,history/?action=view |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131193503/http://www.sztetl.org.pl/en/article/tarnopol/5,history/?action=view |archivedate=2017-01-31 |access-date=2019-03-19 }}</ref>其中三分之一被{{tsl|en|Ukrainian People's Militia|乌克兰人民民兵|乌克兰民兵}}杀害；{{r|YV-Tarnopol}}部分受害者被斩首。<ref name="haaretz2009">[https://web.archive.org/web/20090521113606/http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/1086259.html Talking with the willing executioners.] Haaretz.com 18 May 2009 via Internet Archive.</ref>剩下的三分之二受害者由党卫队在同一周内枪杀。<ref name="YV-Tarnopol">{{cite web |title=Tarnopol Historical Background|url=http://www.yadvashem.org/yv/en/righteous/stories/historical_background/tarnopol.asp |publisher=Yad Vashem |id=Archived 9 March 2014 |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140309114003/http://www.yadvashem.org/yv/en/righteous/stories/historical_background/tarnopol.asp |archivedate=March 9, 2014 }}</ref>1941年10月12日，在[[波兰前东部领土|波兰前东部领土]]的另一座省会城市——[[斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫隔都|斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫]]（现乌克兰[[伊万诺-弗兰科夫斯克|伊万诺-弗兰科夫斯克]]）——发生了[[莱茵哈德行动|莱茵哈德行动]]之前单次屠杀波兰犹太人数最多的[[斯坦尼斯瓦乌夫隔都大屠杀|屠杀事件]]。这次称作“血腥星期天”的屠杀行动由[[秩序警察|秩序警察]]、[[保安警察_(纳粹德国)|安全警察]]与自利沃夫赶来的{{tsl|en|Ukrainian Auxiliary Police|乌克兰辅助警察|乌克兰辅警}}共同实施；作为刑场的公墓旁边设有放着伏特加和三明治的野餐桌，供需要在震耳欲聋的枪声中休息的处决者使用。在夜幕降临前，有12,000名犹太人被杀害。<ref name="yadvashem-Pohl">{{cite book |first=Dieter |last=Pohl |title=Hans Krueger and the Murder of the Jews in the Stanislawow Region |publisher=Yad Vashem Resource Center |url=http://yad-vashem.org.il/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%202292.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812141624/http://yad-vashem.org.il/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%202292.pdf |archive-date=12 August 2014 |via=direct download, PDF 95 KB |pages=12/13, 17/18, 21 |quote=It is clear that a massacre of such proportions under German civil administration was virtually unprecedented.}}<br>{{cite web |author=Andrea Löw |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia –Stanislawów (now Ivano-Frankivsk) |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |url=https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10007236 |accessdate=1 May 2016 |id=From ''{{tsl|en|Encyclopedia of Camps and Ghettos, 1933–1945||The USHMM Encyclopedia of Camps and Ghettos, 1933–1945}}'' |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202061403/https://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10007236 |archivedate=February 2, 2017 }}</ref>

{{tsl|en|Belarusian Auxiliary Police|白俄罗斯辅助警察|白俄罗斯}}、{{tsl|en|Lithuanian Auxiliary Police Battalions|立陶宛辅助警察营|立陶宛}}与乌克兰的{{tsl|en|Schutzmannschaft|辅助警察(纳粹德国)|辅助警察}}（Schuma）共同在波兰东部地区参与了31起致命的反犹骚乱。<ref>{{harvp|Piotrowski|1998|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=hC0-dk7vpM8C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=fifty-one%20pogroms&f=false  ''Poland's Holocaust'', page 209.]}}.另见：{{cite web |title=German-Belarusian Alliance|trans-title=Idea sojuszu niemiecko-białoruskiego |work=Okupacja niemiecka na Białorusi |publisher=Związek Białoruski w RP; Katedra Kultury Białoruskiej {{tsl|en|University of Białystok||Uniwersytetu w Białymstoku}} |via=Internet Archive |year=2007 |author=Eugeniusz Mironowicz |url=http://autary.iig.pl/mironowicz_e/knihi07-26.htm |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927221149/http://autary.iig.pl/mironowicz_e/knihi07-26.htm |archivedate=September 27, 2007 }}</ref>从德国人那里学到的种族灭绝技术——例如先进的{{tsl|en|Pacification actions in German-occupied Poland|德占波兰的平定行动|平定行动计划}}、选址和突然的包围——成为了[[烏克蘭反抗軍|烏克蘭反抗軍]]1943年3月开始的[[瓦莱尼亚与东加利西亚波兰人大屠杀|瓦莱尼亚与东加利西亚波兰人与犹太人大屠杀]]的标志。这一屠杀行动与由希姆莱下达的“东方总计划”中的隔都清场行动并行。<ref>{{cite book |last=Snyder|first=Timothy |year=2003 |title=The Reconstruction of Nations. Poland, Ukraine, Lithuania, Belarus, 1569–1999 |publisher=Yale University Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xSpEynLxJ1MC&q=UPA+1943+Jews |isbn=978-0-300-10586-5 |pages=162–170 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603161012/https://books.google.com/books?id=xSpEynLxJ1MC |archivedate=June 3, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Encyclopedia of Jewish Life Before and During the Holocaust |first1=Shmuel |last1=Spector |first2=Geoffrey |last2=Wigoder |publisher=''NYU Press'' |year=2001|isbn=978-0814793787 |page=1627 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tumlOiOZvSUC&q=Himmler+Ostland+ghettoes+July |volume=Volume III |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231083024/http://books.google.com/books?id=tumlOiOZvSUC |archivedate=December 31, 2013 }}</ref>成千上万逃离驱逐行动并藏匿在森林中的犹太人被{{tsl|en|Banderites|班德拉派}}杀害。<ref>{{cite book |title=Stepan Bandera: The Life and Afterlife of a Ukrainian Nationalist : Fascism, Genocide, and Cult |first=Grzegorz |last=Rossolinski |publisher=Columbia University Press |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6OXJCQAAQBAJ&q=thousand+Jews+forests |year=2014 |isbn=978-3838206844 |page=290 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200911010818/https://books.google.com/books?id=6OXJCQAAQBAJ&q=thousand+Jews+forests |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 生还几率 ==
关于犹太人在大屠杀开始后真正的生存机会的问题持续引起历史学家的注意。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}首先，德国人有意让逃离隔都变得非常困难，犹太人在驱逐到灭绝营之前几乎无法逃出隔都。驱逐行动被欺骗性地伪装成“在东方重新安置”。所有通行证都被取消，重建的墙壁减少了大门数量，警察由党卫队队员取代。一些已经被驱逐到特雷布林卡的受害者被迫向家中写信报平安。还有约3,000人进入了德国的“{{tsl|en|Hotel Polski|波兰人酒店}}”陷阱。许多隔都犹太人直到最后才相信正在发生的事情，因为事态实际的结果在当时似乎是不可想象的。{{r|GSPau-JHE}} {{tsl|en|David J. Landau|大卫·朗道}}表示，弱势的犹太领导可能在屠杀中发挥了作用。{{r|resistance}}{{tsl|en|Israel Gutman|以色列·古特曼}}提出了类似观点，认为波兰地下国可能袭击营地并炸毁通往营地的铁轨。但正如保罗森所指出的，这样的想法是后见之明的产物。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}

[[File:Słonim_Ghetto_burning_(1942-06-29).jpg|thumb]]的一座县城。入侵的苏联人在恐怖的气氛下将该市并入了[[白俄罗斯苏维埃社会主义共和国|白俄罗斯苏维埃社会主义共和国]]。{{r|Wegner-74}}]]

大屠杀幸存者的确切人数不详。战争开始后不久，可能有多达30万波兰犹太人逃到苏联占领区，有些估计的数量甚至更高。{{r|Pinchuk}}值得注意的是，逃往东部的犹太人中有很大一部分是没有家人的男女。<ref name="Pinchuk">{{cite book |title=The Nazi Holocaust. Part 8: Bystanders to the Holocaust, Volume 3 |publisher=Walter de Gruyter |pages=1036–1038 |year=1989 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QEKCZTMlNoIC&q=fleeing+East+without+families |first=Ben Cion |last=Pinchuk |chapter=Jewish refugees in Soviet Poland |editor-first=Michael Robert |editor-last=Marrus |isbn=978-3110968682 |quote=The range of differences in estimates might give us an idea of the problem's complexity. Thus, Avraham Pechenik estimated the number of refugees at 1,000,000.<sup>[p.1038]</sup> |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819201519/https://books.google.com/books?id=QEKCZTMlNoIC&q=fleeing+East+without+families |dead-url=no }}</ref>成千上万人后来在[[瓦莱尼亚与东加利西亚波兰人大屠杀|瓦莱尼亚与东加利西亚波兰人大屠杀]]、{{tsl|en|The Holocaust in Belarus|白俄罗斯的犹太人大屠杀|白俄罗斯}}和[[立陶宛猶太人大屠殺|立陶宛猶太人大屠殺]]（参见[[博纳利大屠杀|博纳利大屠杀]]）中死在[[烏克蘭反抗軍|烏克蘭反抗軍]]、{{tsl|en|Tautinio Darbo Apsaugos Batalionas|立陶宛国家劳动保护旅}}（TDA旅）和{{tsl|en|Ypatingasis būrys|立陶宛特别支队}}手上。{{r|Snyder2004}}{{r|Turowski}}波兰总督府中的大多数波兰犹太人都留在了原地。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}在大规模驱逐发生之前，人们认为没有必要离开熟悉的地方。当隔都从外面封锁时，大多数居民依靠走私的食物活着。约有10万名犹太人试图逃离隔都前往“雅利安”一侧的秘密地点；并且与普遍的误解相反，他们被波兰人出卖的风险非常小。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}

据估计，大约有35万波兰犹太人在大屠杀中幸存下来。{{r|Joc/Lew2010}}其中约有23万人在苏联和苏联控制的波兰领土上幸存下来，其中包括逃离德国占领地区的人们。{{r|Joc/Lew2010}}{{r|Tr-Maz}}二战结束后，超过15万（{{tsl|pl|Grzegorz Berendt|戈热戈日·贝伦特|贝伦特}}）-18万（{{tsl|en|David Engel (historian)|大卫·恩格尔(历史学家)|恩格尔}}）波兰犹太人被遣返或驱逐回新独立的波兰，红军1940年至1941年间从波兰前东部领土征召的年轻人也被遣返。他们的家人大多在大屠杀中丧生。{{r|Berendt}}古纳尔·保罗森估计有3万名波兰犹太人在劳改营中幸存；{{r|GSPau-JHE}}但根据{{tsl|en|David Engel (historian)|大卫·恩格尔(历史学家)|恩格尔}}的说法，仅在德国和奥地利的营地中就有多达7万-8万人被解放，而且对于那些不打算返回的人而言，宣布自己的国籍无济于事。{{r|Engel2005}}{{tsl|en|Czesław Madajczyk|切斯瓦夫·马达伊奇克}}估计，多达11万波兰犹太人在流离失所者营地。{{r|Nazism2000}}根据隆格里奇的说法，多达5万名犹太人在森林中幸存（不计算加利西亚）{{r|Long748}}，也有的在斯大林组建的亲苏的波兰“[[波兰人民军|贝林格军]]”中重返波兰。成功藏匿在隔都“雅利安人”一侧的犹太人可能高达10万人（{{tsl|en|Peter Longerich|彼得·隆格里奇}}），<ref name="Long748">{{cite book |title=Holocaust: The Nazi Persecution and Murder of the Jews |first=Peter |last=Longerich |publisher=OUP Oxford |year=2010 |page=748|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ry-qW0lw2ZAC&lpg=PT748&vq=thousands%20100%2C000%20Paulsson%20conclussion&pg=PT748 |isbn=978-0191613470 |ref=harv |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521074211/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ry-qW0lw2ZAC |archivedate=May 21, 2016 }}</ref>尽管由许多人被德国猎兵杀害。{{r|Long748}}战争结束后，并非所有幸存者都在{{tsl|en|CKŻP|波兰犹太人中央委员会}}（CKŻP）登记。数千名所谓的修道院儿童在战时被非犹太波兰人和天主教会藏匿起来，战后仍然留在{{tsl|en|Franciscan Sisters of the Family of Mary|方济各玛丽家庭姊妹会|玛丽家庭姊妹会}}在20多个地方经营的孤儿院，<ref>{{harvp|Phayer|2000|pp=113, 117–120, 250. |ps= In January 1941 Jan Dobraczynski placed roughly 2,500 children in cooperating convents of Warsaw. Getter took many of them into her convent. During the [[華沙猶太區起義|Ghetto uprising]] the number of Jewish orphans in their care surged upward.<sup>[p.120]</sup>}}</ref>其他天主教修道院也有相似行为。<ref>{{harvp|Bogner|2012|pp=41–44}}.</ref><ref>{{harvp|Paul|2009|pp=16, 63–71, 98, 185. |ps= Despite the fact that at least several hundred {{tsl|en|Franciscan Sisters of the Family of Mary||Sisters of the Family of Mary}} risked their lives to rescue Jews, only three of them, Mother{{tsl|en|Matylda Getter||Matylda Getter}} of Warsaw, Sister Helena Chmielewska of Podhajce, and Sister Celina Kędzierska of Sambor ''(see: {{tsl|en|Sambor Ghetto||Sambor Ghetto}})'' have been decorated by Yad Vashem.<sup>[p. 84]</sup>}}.</ref><!--鉴于旨在防止犹太人生还的德国措施的严重程度，犹太逃犯的存活率已经算是相对较高的；就目前的研究而言，能够躲过驱逐行动的人有最成功的生还几率。{{r|GSPau-JHE}}<ref name="snyder-nyrb">{{cite journal |title=Hitler's Logical Holocaust |journal=The New York Review of Books |first=Timothy |last=Snyder |date=December 20, 2012|url=http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2012/dec/20/hitlers-logical-holocaust/ |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121204172810/http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2012/dec/20/hitlers-logical-holocaust/ |archivedate=December 4, 2012}}</ref> -->

==国界变化与遣返==
{{main|{{tsl|en|Territorial changes of Poland immediately after World War II|第二次世界大战后波兰的领土变更}}|阿利亞運動}}

被列为最高机密的1939年[[苏德互不侵犯条约|苏德互不侵犯条约]]为第二次世界大战铺平了道路，而西方各国对该条约一无所知。<ref name="usds">{{cite journal |title=The Tehran Conference, 1943 |journal=1937–1945 Milestones |author=U.S. Department of State |url=https://history.state.gov/milestones/1937-1945/tehran-conf |year=2015|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151026032152/https://history.state.gov/milestones/1937-1945/tehran-conf |archivedate=October 26, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Property restitution/compensation in Poland |url=http://shoahlegacy.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Property-restitution-in-Poland-for-Green-Paper_05112013.pdf |journal=European Shoah Legacy Institute |author=ESLI |date=July 2014 |via=Internet Archive |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906004023/http://shoahlegacy.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Property-restitution-in-Poland-for-Green-Paper_05112013.pdf|archivedate=September 6, 2015 }}</ref>1945年5月[[德國無條件投降書|德国投降]]后，欧洲的政治地理发生了巨大变化。{{r|Lukas1989}}{{r|Nazism2000}}约瑟夫·斯大林在[[德黑兰会议|德黑兰会议]]期间提出了重新绘制了波兰边界的要求，并在1945年的[[雅尔塔会议|雅尔塔会议]]上确认没有任何商量余地；盟国根据斯大林的要求重新划定了边界。{{r|BP285}}[[波蘭流亡政府|波蘭流亡政府]]被排除在谈判之外。{{r|Fertacz}}波兰的领土减少了大约20％.{{r|Slay2014}}截至1946年底，约有180万波兰公民{{tsl|en|Polish population transfers (1944–1946)|波兰人口迁移(1944-1946)|被驱逐出境并被强行安置}}在新的边界内。<ref name="BP285">{{cite book |title=Warlords: An Extraordinary Re-Creation of World War II |first1=Simon |last1=Berthon |first2=Joanna |last2=Potts |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=q45EBArmpRYC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA285#v=onepage&q=Livadia+Palace,+Poland&f=false |page=285 |publisher=Da Capo Press |year=2007 |isbn=978-0306816505}}</ref><ref name="Fertacz">{{cite journal |first=Sylwester |last=Fertacz |year=2005 |url=http://www.alfa.com.pl/slask/200506/s19.html |trans-title=Krojenie mapy Polski: Bolesna granica |title=Carving of Poland's map |journal=Magazyn Społeczno-Kulturalny ''Śląsk'' |via=[[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]], June 5, 2016. |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425133017/http://www.alfa.com.pl/slask/200506/s19.html |archivedate=April 25, 2009 }}</ref>在强权措施下，波兰在历史上第一次成为同质的[[民族國家|民族國家]]。波兰的金融体系遭到破坏，国民财富减少了38％.新波兰人口减少了约33％，知识分子与犹太人一起被大量消灭。{{r|Slay2014}}

[[File:Zegota(Rada_Pomocy_Zydom)1946.jpg|thumb]]纪念日，{{tsl|en|Żegota|热戈塔委员会}}成员在{{tsl|en|Polish Theatre in Warsaw|华沙波兰剧院}}聚会。]]

由于外部强加的领土转移，波兰的大屠杀幸存者的具体数量仍有争议。{{r|Nazism2000}}据官方统计，该国犹太人的数量在很短的时间内发生了巨大变化。{{r|DHak70}}1946年1月，{{tsl|en|Central Committee of Polish Jews|波兰犹太人中央委员会}}（CKŻP）登记了来自附近的第一批约8.6万名幸存者。到了当年夏天结束时，这个数字上升到大约20.5-21万（注册人数为24万，重复登记数量超过3万）。{{r|DeHakoh2003}}幸存者包括18万名由[[寇松線|苏联控制的领土]]因{{tsl|en|Polish population transfers (1944–1946)|波兰人口迁移(1944-1946)|遣返协议}}而来的犹太人。十年后，[[赫鲁晓夫解冻|斯大林主义的迫害结束]]后，又有3万名犹太人从苏联返回波兰。{{r|Engel2005}}{{r|DeHakoh2003}}

===欧洲的“阿利亚B运动”===

1946年7月，在意在巩固波兰共产党掌权的[[1946年波兰人民公投|作假公投]]之后不久，四十名犹太人和两名波兰人在[[凯尔采反犹骚乱|凯尔采反犹骚乱]]中丧生。{{r|ipn2008}}11名受害者死于刺刀伤口，还有11名因军用突击步枪的枪伤丧命（根据[[国家记忆研究院|IPN]]的官方调查结果），表明正规部队直接参与了骚乱。<ref name="ipn2008">{{cite journal |author1-first=Andrzej |author1-last=Jankowski |author2-first=Leszek |author2-last=Bukowski |date=4 July 2008 |title=The Kielce pogrom as told by the eyewitness |trans-title=Pogrom kielecki – oczami świadka |journal=Niezalezna Gazeta Polska |pp=1–8 |url=http://pamiec.pl/download/49/27596/IPN2920080704.pdf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826073423/http://pamiec.pl/download/49/27596/IPN2920080704.pdf |archivedate=2016-08-26 |access-date=2019-03-19 }} ''Also in'' {{cite book |year=2008 |title=Around the Kielce pogrom |trans-title=Wokół pogromu kieleckiego |others=with Foreword by Jan Żaryn |volume=2 |publisher=IPN |isbn=978-83-60464-87-8 |pp=166–71 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=xgI_AQAAIAAJ&q=zabitych+4+lipca+1946 }}</ref>骚乱促使战时华沙出身的[[波兰工人党|波兰工人党]]将军[[马里安·斯彼哈尔斯基|马里安·斯彼哈尔斯基]]<ref name="TWł2010">{{cite journal |first=Tamara |last=Włodarczyk |title=Osiedle żydowskie na Dolnym Śląsku w latach 1945–1950 (na przykładzie Kłodzka) |journal=Bricha (2.10) |quote=''The decision originated from the military circles (and not the party leadership). The {{tsl|en|Berihah||Berihah}} organization under Cwi Necer was requested to keep the involvement of MSZ and MON a secret.''<sup>(24 in PDF)</sup> ''The migration reached its zenith in 1946, resulting in 150,000 Jews leaving Poland.''<sup>(21 in PDF)</sup> |id=pp. 36, 44–45 (23–24 in PDF) |url=http://www.bibliotekacyfrowa.pl/Content/37156/004.pdf |year=2010 |ref=harv|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413055637/http://www.bibliotekacyfrowa.pl/Content/37156/004.pdf |archivedate=April 13, 2016 }}</ref>签署一项法令，允许剩余的幸存者在没有西方签证或波兰出境许可的情况下离开波兰。{{r|Kochavi-175}}{{r|DeHakoh2003}}波兰是唯一一个允许犹太人自由开展前往[[巴勒斯坦託管地|巴勒斯坦託管地]]的[[阿利亞運動|阿利亞運動]]的[[東方集團|東方集團]]国家；斯大林勉为其难地批准了这类行为，试图削弱英国在中东的影响力。{{r|Engel2005}}<ref name="DHak70">{{harvp|Hakohen|2003|p=70|loc=[https://books.google.com/books?id=hCw6v0TFhdMC&pg=PA70&dq=%22Poland+opened+its+gates+to+Jewish+emigration.%22 'Poland'.]}}</ref>越过波苏新边界的大多数难民在没有有效护照的情况下离开波兰。{{r|DeHakoh2003}}相比之下，经过[[雅尔塔会议|雅尔塔会议]]的准许，苏联强制将本国犹太人从{{tsl|en|DP camp|流离失所营}}带回苏联，而不顾他们的意愿。.<ref name=Kochavi-15>{{cite book |first=Arieh J. |last=Kochavi |title=Post-Holocaust politics: Britain, the United States & Jewish refugees, 1945–1948 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LdWSwGaSoJAC&pg=PA15&dq=%22Soviet+citizens+had+been+returned+irrespective%22 |page=15 |publisher=The [[北卡罗来纳大学系统|University of North Carolina]] Press |isbn=978-0-8078-2620-1 |date=2011 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726054541/https://books.google.com/books?id=LdWSwGaSoJAC&pg=PA15&dq=%22Soviet+citizens+had+been+returned+irrespective%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

波兰边境上的不间断交通急剧增加。{{r|Marrus}}{{r|Engel2005}}<ref name="Ther-Siljak">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oGmTs2SceAgC&pg=PA137&dq=%22agreements+on+the%22+%22mutual+evacuation+of+citizens%22 |title=Redrawing nations: ethnic cleansing in East-Central Europe, 1944–1948 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |year=2001 |first2=Philipp |last2=Ther |first1=Ana |last1=Siljak |page=138 |isbn=978-0-7425-1094-4 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819165420/https://books.google.com/books?id=oGmTs2SceAgC&pg=PA137&dq=%22agreements+on+the%22+%22mutual+evacuation+of+citizens%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>到1947年春天，只有9万犹太人仍留在波兰。<ref name="MS109">{{cite book |first=Michael C. |last=Steinlauf |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U6KVOsjpP0MC&pg=PA109&dq=%22began+to+emerge+from+concentration+camps+and+places+of+refuge%22 |title=Poland |id=In: David S. Wyman, Charles H. Rosenzveig. ''The World Reacts to the Holocaust''. The Johns Hopkins University Press |year=1996 |isbn=9780801849695 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819234903/https://books.google.com/books?id=U6KVOsjpP0MC&pg=PA109&dq=%22began+to+emerge+from+concentration+camps+and+places+of+refuge%22 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{harvp|Lukas|1989}}; ''also in'' {{harvp|Lukas|2001|p=13}}.</ref><ref name="Stankowski">Albert Stankowski, with August Grabski and Grzegorz Berendt; ''Studia z historii Żydów w Polsce po 1945 roku'', Warszawa, {{tsl|en|Żydowski Instytut Historyczny||Żydowski Instytut Historyczny}} 2000, pp. 107–111. {{ISBN|83-85888-36-5}}</ref>英国要求波兰（以及其他国家）制止犹太人的外流，但他们的压力基本上没有成功。{{r|Kochavi-xi}}凯尔采教区在公开声明中谴责了凯尔采的大屠杀。在这封向所有教堂发表的声明中，教区谴责了反犹骚乱。{{tsl|pl|Natalia Aleksiun|娜塔莉亚·阿列克逊}}写道，声明“强调最重要的天主教价值观是对人类同胞的同情，和对人类生命的尊重。它还提到了反犹太暴力的败坏道德的影响，因为暴行发生在青年和孩子面前。”牧师们在[[弥撒|弥撒]]期间不予置评地阅读了公开声明，暗示“反犹骚乱可能实际上是一种政治挑拨。”{{r|Consonni05}}

1947年至1948年期间，大约7,000名服役年龄的犹太男女离开波兰前往[[巴勒斯坦託管地|巴勒斯坦託管地]]。他们是在波兰接受训练的[[哈加拿|哈加拿]]组织的成员，在[[下西里西亚|下西里西亚]]的[[博爾庫夫|博爾庫夫]]训练营由波兰犹太教官训练。[[哈加拿|哈加拿]]由[[美犹联合救济委员会|美犹联合救济委员会]]与波兰政府达成协议提供资金。训练计划一直持续到至1949年初，主要训练22-25岁的男子，以备在[[以色列國防軍|以色列國防軍]]服役。.<ref>{{cite book |title=Iron Curtain: The Crushing of Eastern Europe, 1944–1956 |first=Anne |last=Applebaum |publisher=Knopf Doubleday |year=2012 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DoSGzXQln_oC&lpg=PR48&vq=Bolk%C3%B3w&pg=PR48 |page=48 |isbn=978-0385536431 |access-date=2019-03-19 |archive-date=2019-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005063502/https://books.google.com/books?id=DoSGzXQln_oC&lpg=PR48&vq=Bolk%C3%B3w&pg=PR48 |dead-url=no }}</ref>加入培训是离开波兰的一种便捷方式，因为课程毕业生不受边境管控，可携带未申报的贵重物品，甚至是管制枪械。{{r|TWł2010}}

== 大屠杀纪念馆和纪念活动 ==
[[File:Jüdisches_historisches_Museum_Warschau,_IMG_2806.JPG|thumb]]，2013年4月]]

波兰有大量的纪念馆致力于纪念大屠杀。 1948年4月，华沙的{{tsl|en|Monument to the Ghetto Heroes|隔都英雄纪念碑}}揭幕。主要的博物馆包括位于[[奥斯威辛|奥斯威辛]]郊区的{{tsl|en|Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum|奥斯维辛-比克瑙国家博物馆}}，每年有140万游客来访；还有位于华沙隔都旧址上的[[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|波蘭猶太人歷史博物館]]，介绍了波兰犹太人的千年历史。<ref name=AP1>{{cite news |author=The Associated Press |date=June 26, 2007 |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/06/26/AR2007062601145.html |title=Poland's new Jewish museum to mark community's thousand-year history |others=Ryan Lucas, Warsaw  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214061606/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/06/26/AR2007062601145.html |archivedate=December 14, 2017 }}</ref><ref name=Core>[[波蘭猶太人歷史博物館|POLIN Museum of the History of Polish Jews]](2014), [http://www.polin.pl/en/exhibitions/core-exhibition-grand-opening-october-28-2014 "Core Exhibition."]{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210010803/http://www.polin.pl/en/exhibitions/core-exhibition-grand-opening-october-28-2014 |date=December 10, 2014 }}</ref>自1988年以来，一年一度的名为“{{tsl|en|March of the Living|生者之旅}}”的国际活动于4月的大屠杀纪念日在[[奥斯威辛集中营|奥斯维辛-比克瑙]]旧址举行，共有超过15万名来自世界各地的年轻人参加。<ref name="motl.org">{{cite web |url=http://motl.org/ |title=History of the Holocaust. Remembering the Past, Ensuring the Future |publisher=International March of the Living 2012–2013 |work=Open registration |accessdate=January 5, 2013|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130115111824/http://motl.org/ |archivedate=January 15, 2013 }}</ref>

莱因哈德行动的每个灭绝营都建有国家博物馆。其中，卢布林的{{tsl|en|Majdanek State Museum|马伊达内克国家博物馆}}早在1946年就被宣布为国家纪念馆，其中有完整的二战时期的毒气室和火葬场。马伊达内克博物馆的分馆包括贝乌热茨博物馆及{{tsl|en|Sobibór Museum|索比布尔博物馆}}；以色列和波兰的考古学家正在索比布尔的博物馆进行先进的地球物理研究。<ref name="Haaretz">{{cite news |title=Archaeologists find escape tunnel at Sobibor death camp |publisher=Haaretz Daily Newspaper |date=Jun 7, 2013 |author=Nir Hasson |url=http://www.haaretz.com/jewish-world/jewish-world-news/archeologists-find-escape-tunnel-at-sobibor-death-camp.premium-1.528438 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130714223157/http://www.haaretz.com/jewish-world/jewish-world-news/archeologists-find-escape-tunnel-at-sobibor-death-camp.premium-1.528438 |archivedate=July 14, 2013 |newspaper=Haaretz }}</ref>新的[[特雷布林卡灭绝营|特雷布林卡]]博物馆于2006年对外开放，后来扩建并成为位于一座原[[地方政府大樓|地方政府大樓]]中的[[謝德爾采|謝德爾采]]地区博物馆的一座分馆。（另见{{tsl|en|Siedlce Ghetto|谢德尔采隔都}}）。<ref name="memorialmuseums.org">{{cite web |title=Treblinka Museum of Struggle and Martyrdom |author=Memorial Museums.org|url=http://www.memorialmuseums.org/eng/staettens/view/59/Treblinka-Museum-of-Struggle-and-Martyrdom |publisher=Portal to European Sites of Remembrance |year=2013|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306161036/http://memorialmuseums.org/eng/staettens/view/59/treblinka-museum-of-struggle-and-martyrdom|archivedate=March 6, 2016 }}</ref><ref name="MWiMT">{{cite web |title=The Memorial |url=http://www.treblinka.bho.pl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=203&Itemid=129 |publisher=''Muzeum Walki i Męczeństwa w Treblince. Oddział Muzeum Regionalnego w Siedlcach'' [Museum of Struggle and Martyrdom at Treblinka. Division of the Regional Museum in Siedlce] |date=4 February 2010 |author=Kopówka, Edward |work=''Treblinka. Nigdy wiecej'', Siedlce 2002, pp. 5–54. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019060357/http://www.treblinka.bho.pl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=203&Itemid=129 |archivedate=2013-10-19 |accessdate=2019-03-19 }}</ref>[[内尔河畔海乌姆诺|内尔河畔海乌姆诺]]也设有一座[[内尔河畔海乌姆诺|小型博物馆]]。

{{tsl|en|Radegast train station|拉的加斯特火车站}}是位于[[罗兹_(波兰)|罗兹]]的一处大屠杀纪念地。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.centrumdialogu.com/en/memorial/radegast-station |title=Memorial Radegast station |publisher=Centrum Dialogu im. Marka Edelmana w Łodzi |date=2013 |accessdate=2 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203013353/http://www.centrumdialogu.com/en/memorial/radegast-station |archivedate=3 December 2013 }}</ref> 

[[辛德勒工廠|辛德勒工廠]]涵盖了[[克拉科夫|克拉科夫]]的大屠杀历史。<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2010/aug/15/unlikely-hero/ | title=Schindler factory opens as Holocaust memorial | the Spokesman-Review | access-date=2019-03-19 | archive-date=2021-01-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128000344/https://www.spokesman.com/stories/2010/aug/15/unlikely-hero/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

